49 /// Remove elements from the input array corresponding to set bits in
50 /// `indicesToDrop`, returning the elements not mentioned.
51 template <typename T>
52 static SmallVector<T>
53 removeElementsAtIndices(ArrayRef<T> input,
54  const llvm::BitVector &indicesToDrop) {
55 #ifndef NDEBUG
56  if (!input.empty()) {
57  int lastIndex = indicesToDrop.find_last();
58  if (lastIndex >= 0)
59  assert((size_t)lastIndex < input.size() && "index out of range");
60  }
61 #endif
62 
63  // If the input is empty (which is an optimization we do for certain array
64  // attributes), simply return an empty vector.
65  if (input.empty())
66  return {};
67 
68  // Copy over the live chunks.
69  size_t lastCopied = 0;
70  SmallVector<T> result;
71  result.reserve(input.size() - indicesToDrop.count());
72 
73  for (unsigned indexToDrop : indicesToDrop.set_bits()) {
74  // If we skipped over some valid elements, copy them over.
75  if (indexToDrop > lastCopied) {
76  result.append(input.begin() + lastCopied, input.begin() + indexToDrop);
77  lastCopied = indexToDrop;
78  }
79  // Ignore this value so we don't copy it in the next iteration.
80  ++lastCopied;
81  }
82 
83  // If there are live elements at the end, copy them over.
84  if (lastCopied < input.size())
85  result.append(input.begin() + lastCopied, input.end());
86 
87  return result;
88 }

99 bool firrtl::isDuplexValue(Value val) {
100  // Block arguments are not duplex values.
101  while (Operation *op = val.getDefiningOp()) {
102  auto isDuplex =
103  TypeSwitch<Operation *, std::optional<bool>>(op)
104  .Case<SubfieldOp, SubindexOp, SubaccessOp>([&val](auto op) {
105  val = op.getInput();
106  return std::nullopt;
107  })
108  .Case<RegOp, RegResetOp, WireOp>([](auto) { return true; })
109  .Default([](auto) { return false; });
110  if (isDuplex)
111  return *isDuplex;
112  }
113  return false;
114 }

116 /// Return the kind of port this is given the port type from a 'mem' decl.
117 static MemOp::PortKind getMemPortKindFromType(FIRRTLType type) {
118  constexpr unsigned int addr = 1 << 0;
119  constexpr unsigned int en = 1 << 1;
120  constexpr unsigned int clk = 1 << 2;
121  constexpr unsigned int data = 1 << 3;
122  constexpr unsigned int mask = 1 << 4;
123  constexpr unsigned int rdata = 1 << 5;
124  constexpr unsigned int wdata = 1 << 6;
125  constexpr unsigned int wmask = 1 << 7;
126  constexpr unsigned int wmode = 1 << 8;
127  constexpr unsigned int def = 1 << 9;
128  // Get the kind of port based on the fields of the Bundle.
129  auto portType = type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(type);
130  if (!portType)
131  return MemOp::PortKind::Debug;
132  unsigned fields = 0;
133  // Get the kind of port based on the fields of the Bundle.
134  for (auto elem : portType.getElements()) {
135  fields |= llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(elem.name.getValue())
136  .Case("addr", addr)
137  .Case("en", en)
138  .Case("clk", clk)
139  .Case("data", data)
140  .Case("mask", mask)
141  .Case("rdata", rdata)
142  .Case("wdata", wdata)
143  .Case("wmask", wmask)
144  .Case("wmode", wmode)
145  .Default(def);
146  }
147  if (fields == (addr | en | clk | data))
148  return MemOp::PortKind::Read;
149  if (fields == (addr | en | clk | data | mask))
150  return MemOp::PortKind::Write;
151  if (fields == (addr | en | clk | wdata | wmask | rdata | wmode))
152  return MemOp::PortKind::ReadWrite;
153  return MemOp::PortKind::Debug;
154 }

156 Flow firrtl::swapFlow(Flow flow) {
157  switch (flow) {
158  case Flow::None:
159  return Flow::None;
160  case Flow::Source:
161  return Flow::Sink;
162  case Flow::Sink:
163  return Flow::Source;
164  case Flow::Duplex:
165  return Flow::Duplex;
166  }
167 }

169 constexpr const char *toString(Flow flow) {
170  switch (flow) {
171  case Flow::None:
172  return "no flow";
173  case Flow::Source:
174  return "source flow";
175  case Flow::Sink:
176  return "sink flow";
177  case Flow::Duplex:
178  return "duplex flow";
179  }

182 Flow firrtl::foldFlow(Value val, Flow accumulatedFlow) {
183 
184  if (auto blockArg = dyn_cast<BlockArgument>(val)) {
185  auto *op = val.getParentBlock()->getParentOp();
186  if (auto moduleLike = dyn_cast<FModuleLike>(op)) {
187  auto direction = moduleLike.getPortDirection(blockArg.getArgNumber());
188  if (direction == Direction::Out)
189  return swapFlow(accumulatedFlow);
190  }
191  return accumulatedFlow;
192  }
193 
194  Operation *op = val.getDefiningOp();
195 
196  return TypeSwitch<Operation *, Flow>(op)
197  .Case<SubfieldOp, OpenSubfieldOp>([&](auto op) {
198  return foldFlow(op.getInput(), op.isFieldFlipped()
199  ? swapFlow(accumulatedFlow)
200  : accumulatedFlow);
201  })
202  .Case<SubindexOp, SubaccessOp, OpenSubindexOp, RefSubOp>(
203  [&](auto op) { return foldFlow(op.getInput(), accumulatedFlow); })
204  // Registers, Wires, and behavioral memory ports are always Duplex.
205  .Case<RegOp, RegResetOp, WireOp, MemoryPortOp>(
206  [](auto) { return Flow::Duplex; })
207  .Case<InstanceOp, InstanceChoiceOp>([&](auto inst) {
208  auto resultNo = cast<OpResult>(val).getResultNumber();
209  if (inst.getPortDirection(resultNo) == Direction::Out)
210  return accumulatedFlow;
211  return swapFlow(accumulatedFlow);
212  })
213  .Case<MemOp>([&](auto op) {
214  // only debug ports with RefType have source flow.
215  if (type_isa<RefType>(val.getType()))
216  return Flow::Source;
217  return swapFlow(accumulatedFlow);
218  })
219  .Case<ObjectSubfieldOp>([&](ObjectSubfieldOp op) {
220  auto input = op.getInput();
221  auto *inputOp = input.getDefiningOp();
222 
223  // We are directly accessing a port on a local declaration.
224  if (auto objectOp = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjectOp>(inputOp)) {
225  auto classType = input.getType();
226  auto direction = classType.getElement(op.getIndex()).direction;
227  if (direction == Direction::In)
228  return Flow::Sink;
229  return Flow::Source;
230  }
231 
232  // We are accessing a remote object. Input ports on remote objects are
233  // inaccessible, and thus have Flow::None. Walk backwards through the
234  // chain of subindexes, to detect if we have indexed through an input
235  // port. At the end, either we did index through an input port, or the
236  // entire path was through output ports with source flow.
237  while (true) {
238  auto classType = input.getType();
239  auto direction = classType.getElement(op.getIndex()).direction;
240  if (direction == Direction::In)
241  return Flow::None;
242 
243  op = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjectSubfieldOp>(inputOp);
244  if (op) {
245  input = op.getInput();
246  inputOp = input.getDefiningOp();
247  continue;
248  }
249 
250  return accumulatedFlow;
251  };
252  })
253  // Anything else acts like a universal source.
254  .Default([&](auto) { return accumulatedFlow; });
255 }

257 // TODO: This is doing the same walk as foldFlow. These two functions can be
258 // combined and return a (flow, kind) product.
259 DeclKind firrtl::getDeclarationKind(Value val) {
260  Operation *op = val.getDefiningOp();
261  if (!op)
262  return DeclKind::Port;
263 
264  return TypeSwitch<Operation *, DeclKind>(op)
265  .Case<InstanceOp>([](auto) { return DeclKind::Instance; })
266  .Case<SubfieldOp, SubindexOp, SubaccessOp, OpenSubfieldOp, OpenSubindexOp,
267  RefSubOp>([](auto op) { return getDeclarationKind(op.getInput()); })
268  .Default([](auto) { return DeclKind::Other; });
269 }

284 /// Check whether a block argument ("port") or the operation defining a value
285 /// has a `DontTouch` annotation, or a symbol that should prevent certain types
286 /// of canonicalizations.
287 bool firrtl::hasDontTouch(Value value) {
288  if (auto *op = value.getDefiningOp())
289  return hasDontTouch(op);
290  auto arg = dyn_cast<BlockArgument>(value);
291  auto module = cast<FModuleOp>(arg.getOwner()->getParentOp());
292  return (module.getPortSymbolAttr(arg.getArgNumber())) ||
293  AnnotationSet::forPort(module, arg.getArgNumber()).hasDontTouch();
294 }

296 /// Get a special name to use when printing the entry block arguments of the
297 /// region contained by an operation in this dialect.
298 void getAsmBlockArgumentNamesImpl(Operation *op, mlir::Region &region,
299  OpAsmSetValueNameFn setNameFn) {
300  if (region.empty())
301  return;
302  auto *parentOp = op;
303  auto *block = &region.front();
304  // Check to see if the operation containing the arguments has 'firrtl.name'
305  // attributes for them. If so, use that as the name.
306  auto argAttr = parentOp->getAttrOfType<ArrayAttr>("portNames");
307  // Do not crash on invalid IR.
308  if (!argAttr || argAttr.size() != block->getNumArguments())
309  return;
310 
311  for (size_t i = 0, e = block->getNumArguments(); i != e; ++i) {
312  auto str = cast<StringAttr>(argAttr[i]).getValue();
313  if (!str.empty())
314  setNameFn(block->getArgument(i), str);
315  }
316 }

326 namespace {
327 struct CompareSymbolRefAttr {
328  // True if lhs is lexicographically less than rhs.
329  bool operator()(SymbolRefAttr lhs, SymbolRefAttr rhs) const {
330  auto cmp = lhs.getRootReference().compare(rhs.getRootReference());
331  if (cmp == -1)
332  return true;
333  if (cmp == 1)
334  return false;
335  auto lhsNested = lhs.getNestedReferences();
336  auto rhsNested = rhs.getNestedReferences();
337  auto lhsNestedSize = lhsNested.size();
338  auto rhsNestedSize = rhsNested.size();
339  auto e = std::min(lhsNestedSize, rhsNestedSize);
340  for (unsigned i = 0; i < e; ++i) {
341  auto cmp = lhsNested[i].getAttr().compare(rhsNested[i].getAttr());
342  if (cmp == -1)
343  return true;
344  if (cmp == 1)
345  return false;
346  }
347  return lhsNestedSize < rhsNestedSize;
348  }
349 };
350 } // namespace

352 using LayerSet = SmallSet<SymbolRefAttr, 4, CompareSymbolRefAttr>;
353 
354 /// Get the ambient layers active at the given op.
355 static LayerSet getAmbientLayersAt(Operation *op) {
356  // Crawl through the parent ops, accumulating all ambient layers at the given
357  // operation.
358  LayerSet result;
359  for (; op != nullptr; op = op->getParentOp()) {
360  if (auto module = dyn_cast<FModuleLike>(op)) {
361  auto layers = module.getLayersAttr().getAsRange<SymbolRefAttr>();
362  result.insert(layers.begin(), layers.end());
363  break;
364  }
365  if (auto layerblock = dyn_cast<LayerBlockOp>(op)) {
366  result.insert(layerblock.getLayerName());
367  continue;
368  }
369  }
370  return result;
371 }

373 /// Get the ambient layer requirements at the definition site of the value.
374 static LayerSet getAmbientLayersFor(Value value) {
375  return getAmbientLayersAt(getFieldRefFromValue(value).getDefiningOp());
376 }

378 /// Get the effective layer requirements for the given value.
379 /// The effective layers for a value is the union of
380 /// - the ambient layers for the cannonical storage location.
381 /// - any explicit layer annotations in the value's type.
382 static LayerSet getLayersFor(Value value) {
383  auto result = getAmbientLayersFor(value);
384  if (auto type = dyn_cast<RefType>(value.getType()))
385  if (auto layer = type.getLayer())
386  result.insert(type.getLayer());
387  return result;
388 }

390 /// Check that the source layer is compatible with the destination layer.
391 /// Either the source and destination are identical, or the source-layer
392 /// is a parent of the destination. For example `A` is compatible with `A.B.C`,
393 /// because any definition valid in `A` is also valid in `A.B.C`.
394 static bool isLayerCompatibleWith(mlir::SymbolRefAttr srcLayer,
395  mlir::SymbolRefAttr dstLayer) {
396  // A non-colored probe may be cast to any colored probe.
397  if (!srcLayer)
398  return true;
399 
400  // A colored probe cannot be cast to an uncolored probe.
401  if (!dstLayer)
402  return false;
403 
404  // Return true if the srcLayer is a prefix of the dstLayer.
405  if (srcLayer.getRootReference() != dstLayer.getRootReference())
406  return false;
407 
408  auto srcNames = srcLayer.getNestedReferences();
409  auto dstNames = dstLayer.getNestedReferences();
410  if (dstNames.size() < srcNames.size())
411  return false;
412 
413  return llvm::all_of(llvm::zip_first(srcNames, dstNames),
414  [](auto x) { return std::get<0>(x) == std::get<1>(x); });
415 }
416 
417 /// Check that the source layer is present in the destination layers.
418 static bool isLayerCompatibleWith(SymbolRefAttr srcLayer,
419  const LayerSet &dstLayers) {
420  // fast path: the required layer is directly listed in the provided layers.
421  if (dstLayers.contains(srcLayer))
422  return true;
423 
424  // Slow path: the required layer is not directly listed in the provided
425  // layers, but the layer may still be provided by a nested layer.
426  return any_of(dstLayers, [=](SymbolRefAttr dstLayer) {
427  return isLayerCompatibleWith(srcLayer, dstLayer);
428  });
429 }
430 
431 /// Check that the source layers are all present in the destination layers.
432 /// True if all source layers are present in the destination.
433 /// Outputs the set of source layers that are missing in the destination.
434 static bool isLayerSetCompatibleWith(const LayerSet &src, const LayerSet &dst,
435  SmallVectorImpl<SymbolRefAttr> &missing) {
436  for (auto srcLayer : src)
437  if (!isLayerCompatibleWith(srcLayer, dst))
438  missing.push_back(srcLayer);
439 
440  llvm::sort(missing, CompareSymbolRefAttr());
441  return missing.empty();
442 }

448 void CircuitOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
449  StringAttr name, ArrayAttr annotations) {
450  // Add an attribute for the name.
451  result.addAttribute(builder.getStringAttr("name"), name);
452 
453  if (!annotations)
454  annotations = builder.getArrayAttr({});
455  result.addAttribute("annotations", annotations);
456 
457  // Create a region and a block for the body.
458  Region *bodyRegion = result.addRegion();
459  Block *body = new Block();
460  bodyRegion->push_back(body);
461 }

472 static void printCircuitOpAttrs(OpAsmPrinter &p, Operation *op,
473  DictionaryAttr attr) {
474  // "name" is always elided.
475  SmallVector<StringRef> elidedAttrs = {"name"};
476  // Elide "annotations" if it doesn't exist or if it is empty

484 LogicalResult CircuitOp::verifyRegions() {
485  StringRef main = getName();
486 
487  // Check that the circuit has a non-empty name.
488  if (main.empty()) {
489  emitOpError("must have a non-empty name");
490  return failure();
491  }
492 
493  mlir::SymbolTable symtbl(getOperation());
494 
495  if (!symtbl.lookup(main))
496  return emitOpError().append("Module with same name as circuit not found");
497 
498  // Store a mapping of defname to either the first external module
499  // that defines it or, preferentially, the first external module
500  // that defines it and has no parameters.
501  llvm::DenseMap<Attribute, FExtModuleOp> defnameMap;
502 
503  auto verifyExtModule = [&](FExtModuleOp extModule) -> LogicalResult {
504  if (!extModule)
505  return success();
506 
507  auto defname = extModule.getDefnameAttr();
508  if (!defname)
509  return success();
510 
511  // Check that this extmodule's defname does not conflict with
512  // the symbol name of any module.
513  if (auto collidingModule = symtbl.lookup<FModuleOp>(defname.getValue()))
514  return extModule.emitOpError()
515  .append("attribute 'defname' with value ", defname,
516  " conflicts with the name of another module in the circuit")
517  .attachNote(collidingModule.getLoc())
518  .append("previous module declared here");
519 
520  // Find an optional extmodule with a defname collision. Update
521  // the defnameMap if this is the first extmodule with that
522  // defname or if the current extmodule takes no parameters and
523  // the collision does. The latter condition improves later
524  // extmodule verification as checking against a parameterless
525  // module is stricter.
526  FExtModuleOp collidingExtModule;
527  if (auto &value = defnameMap[defname]) {
528  collidingExtModule = value;
529  if (!value.getParameters().empty() && extModule.getParameters().empty())
530  value = extModule;
531  } else {
532  value = extModule;
533  // Go to the next extmodule if no extmodule with the same
534  // defname was found.
535  return success();
536  }
537 
538  // Check that the number of ports is exactly the same.
539  SmallVector<PortInfo> ports = extModule.getPorts();
540  SmallVector<PortInfo> collidingPorts = collidingExtModule.getPorts();
541 
542  if (ports.size() != collidingPorts.size())
543  return extModule.emitOpError()
544  .append("with 'defname' attribute ", defname, " has ", ports.size(),
545  " ports which is different from a previously defined "
546  "extmodule with the same 'defname' which has ",
547  collidingPorts.size(), " ports")
548  .attachNote(collidingExtModule.getLoc())
549  .append("previous extmodule definition occurred here");
550 
551  // Check that ports match for name and type. Since parameters
552  // *might* affect widths, ignore widths if either module has
553  // parameters. Note that this allows for misdetections, but
554  // has zero false positives.
555  for (auto p : llvm::zip(ports, collidingPorts)) {
556  StringAttr aName = std::get<0>(p).name, bName = std::get<1>(p).name;
557  Type aType = std::get<0>(p).type, bType = std::get<1>(p).type;
558 
559  if (aName != bName)
560  return extModule.emitOpError()
561  .append("with 'defname' attribute ", defname,
562  " has a port with name ", aName,
563  " which does not match the name of the port in the same "
564  "position of a previously defined extmodule with the same "
565  "'defname', expected port to have name ",
566  bName)
567  .attachNote(collidingExtModule.getLoc())
568  .append("previous extmodule definition occurred here");
569 
570  if (!extModule.getParameters().empty() ||
571  !collidingExtModule.getParameters().empty()) {
572  // Compare base types as widthless, others must match.
573  if (auto base = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(aType))
574  aType = base.getWidthlessType();
575  if (auto base = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(bType))
576  bType = base.getWidthlessType();
577  }
578  if (aType != bType)
579  return extModule.emitOpError()
580  .append("with 'defname' attribute ", defname,
581  " has a port with name ", aName,
582  " which has a different type ", aType,
583  " which does not match the type of the port in the same "
584  "position of a previously defined extmodule with the same "
585  "'defname', expected port to have type ",
586  bType)
587  .attachNote(collidingExtModule.getLoc())
588  .append("previous extmodule definition occurred here");
589  }
590  return success();
591  };
592 
593  for (auto &op : *getBodyBlock()) {
594  // Verify external modules.
595  if (auto extModule = dyn_cast<FExtModuleOp>(op)) {
596  if (verifyExtModule(extModule).failed())
597  return failure();
598  }
599  }
600 
601  return success();
602 }

610 static SmallVector<PortInfo> getPortImpl(FModuleLike module) {
611  SmallVector<PortInfo> results;
612  for (unsigned i = 0, e = module.getNumPorts(); i < e; ++i) {
613  results.push_back({module.getPortNameAttr(i), module.getPortType(i),
614  module.getPortDirection(i), module.getPortSymbolAttr(i),
615  module.getPortLocation(i),
616  AnnotationSet::forPort(module, i)});
617  }
618  return results;
619 }

629 static hw::ModulePort::Direction dirFtoH(Direction dir) {
630  if (dir == Direction::In)
631  return hw::ModulePort::Direction::Input;
632  if (dir == Direction::Out)
633  return hw::ModulePort::Direction::Output;
634  assert(0 && "invalid direction");
635  abort();
636 }

638 static SmallVector<hw::PortInfo> getPortListImpl(FModuleLike module) {
639  SmallVector<hw::PortInfo> results;
640  auto aname = StringAttr::get(module.getContext(),
641  hw::HWModuleLike::getPortSymbolAttrName());
642  auto emptyDict = DictionaryAttr::get(module.getContext());
643  for (unsigned i = 0, e = getNumPorts(module); i < e; ++i) {
644  auto sym = module.getPortSymbolAttr(i);
645  results.push_back(
646  {{module.getPortNameAttr(i), module.getPortType(i),
647  dirFtoH(module.getPortDirection(i))},
648  i,
649  sym ? DictionaryAttr::get(
650  module.getContext(),
651  ArrayRef<mlir::NamedAttribute>{NamedAttribute{aname, sym}})
652  : emptyDict,
653  module.getPortLocation(i)});
654  }
655  return results;
656 }

708 /// Inserts the given ports. The insertion indices are expected to be in order.
709 /// Insertion occurs in-order, such that ports with the same insertion index
710 /// appear in the module in the same order they appeared in the list.
711 static void insertPorts(FModuleLike op,
712  ArrayRef<std::pair<unsigned, PortInfo>> ports,
713  bool supportsInternalPaths = false) {
714  if (ports.empty())
715  return;
716  unsigned oldNumArgs = op.getNumPorts();
717  unsigned newNumArgs = oldNumArgs + ports.size();
718 
719  // Add direction markers and names for new ports.
720  auto existingDirections = op.getPortDirectionsAttr();
721  ArrayRef<Attribute> existingNames = op.getPortNames();
722  ArrayRef<Attribute> existingTypes = op.getPortTypes();
723  ArrayRef<Attribute> existingLocs = op.getPortLocations();
724  assert(existingDirections.size() == oldNumArgs);
725  assert(existingNames.size() == oldNumArgs);
726  assert(existingTypes.size() == oldNumArgs);
727  assert(existingLocs.size() == oldNumArgs);
728  SmallVector<Attribute> internalPaths;
729  auto emptyInternalPath = InternalPathAttr::get(op.getContext());
730  if (supportsInternalPaths) {
731  if (auto internalPathsAttr = op->getAttrOfType<ArrayAttr>("internalPaths"))
732  llvm::append_range(internalPaths, internalPathsAttr);
733  else
734  internalPaths.resize(oldNumArgs, emptyInternalPath);
735  assert(internalPaths.size() == oldNumArgs);
736  }
737 
738  SmallVector<bool> newDirections;
739  SmallVector<Attribute> newNames, newTypes, newAnnos, newSyms, newLocs,
740  newInternalPaths;
741  newDirections.reserve(newNumArgs);
742  newNames.reserve(newNumArgs);
743  newTypes.reserve(newNumArgs);
744  newAnnos.reserve(newNumArgs);
745  newSyms.reserve(newNumArgs);
746  newLocs.reserve(newNumArgs);
747  newInternalPaths.reserve(newNumArgs);
748 
749  auto emptyArray = ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), {});
750 
751  unsigned oldIdx = 0;
752  auto migrateOldPorts = [&](unsigned untilOldIdx) {
753  while (oldIdx < oldNumArgs && oldIdx < untilOldIdx) {
754  newDirections.push_back(existingDirections[oldIdx]);
755  newNames.push_back(existingNames[oldIdx]);
756  newTypes.push_back(existingTypes[oldIdx]);
757  newAnnos.push_back(op.getAnnotationsAttrForPort(oldIdx));
758  newSyms.push_back(op.getPortSymbolAttr(oldIdx));
759  newLocs.push_back(existingLocs[oldIdx]);
760  if (supportsInternalPaths)
761  newInternalPaths.push_back(internalPaths[oldIdx]);
762  ++oldIdx;
763  }
764  };
765  for (auto pair : llvm::enumerate(ports)) {
766  auto idx = pair.value().first;
767  auto &port = pair.value().second;
768  migrateOldPorts(idx);
769  newDirections.push_back(direction::unGet(port.direction));
770  newNames.push_back(port.name);
771  newTypes.push_back(TypeAttr::get(port.type));
772  auto annos = port.annotations.getArrayAttr();
773  newAnnos.push_back(annos ? annos : emptyArray);
774  newSyms.push_back(port.sym);
775  newLocs.push_back(port.loc);
776  if (supportsInternalPaths)
777  newInternalPaths.push_back(emptyInternalPath);
778  }
779  migrateOldPorts(oldNumArgs);
780 
781  // The lack of *any* port annotations is represented by an empty
782  // `portAnnotations` array as a shorthand.
783  if (llvm::all_of(newAnnos, [](Attribute attr) {
784  return cast<ArrayAttr>(attr).empty();
785  }))
786  newAnnos.clear();
787 
788  // Apply these changed markers.
789  op->setAttr("portDirections",
790  direction::packAttribute(op.getContext(), newDirections));
791  op->setAttr("portNames", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newNames));
792  op->setAttr("portTypes", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newTypes));
793  op->setAttr("portAnnotations", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newAnnos));
794  op.setPortSymbols(newSyms);
795  op->setAttr("portLocations", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newLocs));
796  if (supportsInternalPaths) {
797  // Drop if all-empty, otherwise set to new array.
798  auto empty = llvm::all_of(newInternalPaths, [](Attribute attr) {
799  return !cast<InternalPathAttr>(attr).getPath();
800  });
801  if (empty)
802  op->removeAttr("internalPaths");
803  else
804  op->setAttr("internalPaths",
805  ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newInternalPaths));
806  }
807 }
808 
809 /// Erases the ports that have their corresponding bit set in `portIndices`.
810 static void erasePorts(FModuleLike op, const llvm::BitVector &portIndices) {
811  if (portIndices.none())
812  return;
813 
814  // Drop the direction markers for dead ports.
815  SmallVector<Direction> portDirections =
816  direction::unpackAttribute(op.getPortDirectionsAttr());
817  ArrayRef<Attribute> portNames = op.getPortNames();
818  ArrayRef<Attribute> portTypes = op.getPortTypes();
819  ArrayRef<Attribute> portAnnos = op.getPortAnnotations();
820  ArrayRef<Attribute> portSyms = op.getPortSymbols();
821  ArrayRef<Attribute> portLocs = op.getPortLocations();
822  auto numPorts = op.getNumPorts();
823  (void)numPorts;
824  assert(portDirections.size() == numPorts);
825  assert(portNames.size() == numPorts);
826  assert(portAnnos.size() == numPorts || portAnnos.empty());
827  assert(portTypes.size() == numPorts);
828  assert(portSyms.size() == numPorts || portSyms.empty());
829  assert(portLocs.size() == numPorts);
830 
831  SmallVector<Direction> newPortDirections =
832  removeElementsAtIndices<Direction>(portDirections, portIndices);
833  SmallVector<Attribute> newPortNames, newPortTypes, newPortAnnos, newPortSyms,
834  newPortLocs;
835  newPortNames = removeElementsAtIndices(portNames, portIndices);
836  newPortTypes = removeElementsAtIndices(portTypes, portIndices);
837  newPortAnnos = removeElementsAtIndices(portAnnos, portIndices);
838  newPortSyms = removeElementsAtIndices(portSyms, portIndices);
839  newPortLocs = removeElementsAtIndices(portLocs, portIndices);
840  op->setAttr("portDirections",
841  direction::packAttribute(op.getContext(), newPortDirections));
842  op->setAttr("portNames", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newPortNames));
843  op->setAttr("portAnnotations", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newPortAnnos));
844  op->setAttr("portTypes", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newPortTypes));
845  FModuleLike::fixupPortSymsArray(newPortSyms, op.getContext());
846  op->setAttr("portSyms", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newPortSyms));
847  op->setAttr("portLocations", ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newPortLocs));
848 }
849 
850 template <typename T>
851 static void eraseInternalPaths(T op, const llvm::BitVector &portIndices) {
852  // Fixup internalPaths array.
853  auto internalPaths = op.getInternalPaths();
854  if (!internalPaths)
855  return;
856 
857  auto newPaths =
858  removeElementsAtIndices(internalPaths->getValue(), portIndices);
859 
860  // Drop if all-empty, otherwise set to new array.
861  auto empty = llvm::all_of(newPaths, [](Attribute attr) {
862  return !cast<InternalPathAttr>(attr).getPath();
863  });
864  if (empty)
865  op.removeInternalPathsAttr();
866  else
867  op.setInternalPathsAttr(ArrayAttr::get(op.getContext(), newPaths));
868 }

889 /// Inserts the given ports. The insertion indices are expected to be in order.
890 /// Insertion occurs in-order, such that ports with the same insertion index
891 /// appear in the module in the same order they appeared in the list.
892 void FModuleOp::insertPorts(ArrayRef<std::pair<unsigned, PortInfo>> ports) {
893  ::insertPorts(cast<FModuleLike>((Operation *)*this), ports);
894 
895  // Insert the block arguments.
896  auto *body = getBodyBlock();
897  for (size_t i = 0, e = ports.size(); i < e; ++i) {
898  // Block arguments are inserted one at a time, so for each argument we
899  // insert we have to increase the index by 1.
900  auto &[index, port] = ports[i];
901  body->insertArgument(index + i, port.type, port.loc);
902  }
903 }

922 static void buildModuleLike(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
923  StringAttr name, ArrayRef<PortInfo> ports,
924  ArrayAttr annotations, ArrayAttr layers,
925  bool withAnnotations, bool withLayers) {
926  // Add an attribute for the name.
927  result.addAttribute(::mlir::SymbolTable::getSymbolAttrName(), name);
928 
929  // Record the names of the arguments if present.
930  SmallVector<Direction, 4> portDirections;
931  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portNames;
932  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portTypes;
933  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portAnnotations;
934  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portSyms;
935  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portLocs;
936  for (const auto &port : ports) {
937  portDirections.push_back(port.direction);
938  portNames.push_back(port.name);
939  portTypes.push_back(TypeAttr::get(port.type));
940  portAnnotations.push_back(port.annotations.getArrayAttr());
941  portSyms.push_back(port.sym);
942  portLocs.push_back(port.loc);
943  }
944 
945  // The lack of *any* port annotations is represented by an empty
946  // `portAnnotations` array as a shorthand.
947  if (llvm::all_of(portAnnotations, [](Attribute attr) {
948  return cast<ArrayAttr>(attr).empty();
949  }))
950  portAnnotations.clear();
951 
952  FModuleLike::fixupPortSymsArray(portSyms, builder.getContext());
953  // Both attributes are added, even if the module has no ports.
954  result.addAttribute(
955  "portDirections",
956  direction::packAttribute(builder.getContext(), portDirections));
957  result.addAttribute("portNames", builder.getArrayAttr(portNames));
958  result.addAttribute("portTypes", builder.getArrayAttr(portTypes));
959  result.addAttribute("portSyms", builder.getArrayAttr(portSyms));
960  result.addAttribute("portLocations", builder.getArrayAttr(portLocs));
961 
962  if (withAnnotations) {
963  if (!annotations)
964  annotations = builder.getArrayAttr({});
965  result.addAttribute("annotations", annotations);
966  result.addAttribute("portAnnotations",
967  builder.getArrayAttr(portAnnotations));
968  }
969 
970  if (withLayers) {
971  if (!layers)
972  layers = builder.getArrayAttr({});
973  result.addAttribute("layers", layers);
974  }
975 
976  result.addRegion();
977 }
978 
979 static void buildModule(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
980  StringAttr name, ArrayRef<PortInfo> ports,
981  ArrayAttr annotations, ArrayAttr layers) {
982  buildModuleLike(builder, result, name, ports, annotations, layers,
983  /*withAnnotations=*/true, /*withLayers=*/true);
984 }

986 static void buildClass(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
987  StringAttr name, ArrayRef<PortInfo> ports) {
988  return buildModuleLike(builder, result, name, ports, {}, {},
989  /*withAnnotations=*/false,
990  /*withLayers=*/false);
991 }

993 void FModuleOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result,
994  StringAttr name, ConventionAttr convention,
995  ArrayRef<PortInfo> ports, ArrayAttr annotations,
996  ArrayAttr layers) {
997  buildModule(builder, result, name, ports, annotations, layers);
998  result.addAttribute("convention", convention);
999 
1000  // Create a region and a block for the body.
1001  auto *bodyRegion = result.regions[0].get();
1002  Block *body = new Block();
1003  bodyRegion->push_back(body);
1004 
1005  // Add arguments to the body block.
1006  for (auto &elt : ports)
1007  body->addArgument(elt.type, elt.loc);
1008 }

1064 /// Print a list of module ports in the following form:
1065 /// in x: !firrtl.uint<1> [{class = "DontTouch}], out "_port": !firrtl.uint<2>
1066 ///
1067 /// When there is no block specified, the port names print as MLIR identifiers,
1068 /// wrapping in quotes if not legal to print as-is. When there is no block
1069 /// specified, this function always return false, indicating that there was no
1070 /// issue printing port names.
1071 ///
1072 /// If there is a block specified, then port names will be printed as SSA
1073 /// values. If there is a reason the printed SSA values can't match the true
1074 /// port name, then this function will return true. When this happens, the
1075 /// caller should print the port names as a part of the `attr-dict`.
1076 static bool
1077 printModulePorts(OpAsmPrinter &p, Block *block, ArrayRef<bool> portDirections,
1078  ArrayRef<Attribute> portNames, ArrayRef<Attribute> portTypes,
1079  ArrayRef<Attribute> portAnnotations,
1080  ArrayRef<Attribute> portSyms, ArrayRef<Attribute> portLocs) {
1081  // When printing port names as SSA values, we can fail to print them
1082  // identically.
1083  bool printedNamesDontMatch = false;
1084 
1085  mlir::OpPrintingFlags flags;
1086 
1087  // If we are printing the ports as block arguments the op must have a first
1088  // block.
1089  SmallString<32> resultNameStr;
1090  p << '(';
1091  for (unsigned i = 0, e = portTypes.size(); i < e; ++i) {
1092  if (i > 0)
1093  p << ", ";
1094 
1095  // Print the port direction.
1096  p << direction::get(portDirections[i]) << " ";
1097 
1098  // Print the port name. If there is a valid block, we print it as a block
1099  // argument.
1100  if (block) {
1101  // Get the printed format for the argument name.
1102  resultNameStr.clear();
1103  llvm::raw_svector_ostream tmpStream(resultNameStr);
1104  p.printOperand(block->getArgument(i), tmpStream);
1105  // If the name wasn't printable in a way that agreed with portName, make
1106  // sure to print out an explicit portNames attribute.
1107  auto portName = cast<StringAttr>(portNames[i]).getValue();
1108  if (!portName.empty() && tmpStream.str().drop_front() != portName)
1109  printedNamesDontMatch = true;
1110  p << tmpStream.str();
1111  } else {
1112  p.printKeywordOrString(cast<StringAttr>(portNames[i]).getValue());
1113  }
1114 
1115  // Print the port type.
1116  p << ": ";
1117  auto portType = cast<TypeAttr>(portTypes[i]).getValue();
1118  p.printType(portType);
1119 
1120  // Print the optional port symbol.
1121  if (!portSyms.empty()) {
1122  if (!portSyms[i].cast<hw::InnerSymAttr>().empty()) {
1123  p << " sym ";
1124  portSyms[i].cast<hw::InnerSymAttr>().print(p);
1125  }
1126  }
1127 
1128  // Print the port specific annotations. The port annotations array will be
1129  // empty if there are none.
1130  if (!portAnnotations.empty() &&
1131  !cast<ArrayAttr>(portAnnotations[i]).empty()) {
1132  p << " ";
1133  p.printAttribute(portAnnotations[i]);
1134  }
1135 
1136  // Print the port location.
1137  // TODO: `printOptionalLocationSpecifier` will emit aliases for locations,
1138  // even if they are not printed. This will have to be fixed upstream. For
1139  // now, use what was specified on the command line.
1140  if (flags.shouldPrintDebugInfo() && !portLocs.empty())
1141  p.printOptionalLocationSpecifier(cast<LocationAttr>(portLocs[i]));
1142  }
1143 
1144  p << ')';
1145  return printedNamesDontMatch;
1146 }

1148 /// Parse a list of module ports. If port names are SSA identifiers, then this
1149 /// will populate `entryArgs`.
1150 static ParseResult
1151 parseModulePorts(OpAsmParser &parser, bool hasSSAIdentifiers,
1152  bool supportsSymbols,
1153  SmallVectorImpl<OpAsmParser::Argument> &entryArgs,
1154  SmallVectorImpl<Direction> &portDirections,
1155  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &portNames,
1156  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &portTypes,
1157  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &portAnnotations,
1158  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &portSyms,
1159  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &portLocs) {
1160  auto *context = parser.getContext();
1161 
1162  auto parseArgument = [&]() -> ParseResult {
1163  // Parse port direction.
1164  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("out")))
1165  portDirections.push_back(Direction::Out);
1166  else if (succeeded(parser.parseKeyword("in", "or 'out'")))
1167  portDirections.push_back(Direction::In);
1168  else
1169  return failure();
1170 
1171  // This is the location or the port declaration in the IR. If there is no
1172  // other location information, we use this to point to the MLIR.
1173  llvm::SMLoc irLoc;
1174 
1175  if (hasSSAIdentifiers) {
1176  OpAsmParser::Argument arg;
1177  if (parser.parseArgument(arg))
1178  return failure();
1179  entryArgs.push_back(arg);
1180 
1181  // The name of an argument is of the form "%42" or "%id", and since
1182  // parsing succeeded, we know it always has one character.
1183  assert(arg.ssaName.name.size() > 1 && arg.ssaName.name[0] == '%' &&
1184  "Unknown MLIR name");
1185  if (isdigit(arg.ssaName.name[1]))
1186  portNames.push_back(StringAttr::get(context, ""));
1187  else
1188  portNames.push_back(
1189  StringAttr::get(context, arg.ssaName.name.drop_front()));
1190 
1191  // Store the location of the SSA name.
1192  irLoc = arg.ssaName.location;
1193 
1194  } else {
1195  // Parse the port name.
1196  irLoc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
1197  std::string portName;
1198  if (parser.parseKeywordOrString(&portName))
1199  return failure();
1200  portNames.push_back(StringAttr::get(context, portName));
1201  }
1202 
1203  // Parse the port type.
1204  Type portType;
1205  if (parser.parseColonType(portType))
1206  return failure();
1207  portTypes.push_back(TypeAttr::get(portType));
1208 
1209  if (hasSSAIdentifiers)
1210  entryArgs.back().type = portType;
1211 
1212  // Parse the optional port symbol.
1213  if (supportsSymbols) {
1214  hw::InnerSymAttr innerSymAttr;
1215  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("sym"))) {
1216  NamedAttrList dummyAttrs;
1217  if (parser.parseCustomAttributeWithFallback(
1218  innerSymAttr, ::mlir::Type{},
1219  hw::InnerSymbolTable::getInnerSymbolAttrName(), dummyAttrs)) {
1220  return ::mlir::failure();
1221  }
1222  }
1223  portSyms.push_back(innerSymAttr);
1224  }
1225 
1226  // Parse the port annotations.
1227  ArrayAttr annos;
1228  auto parseResult = parser.parseOptionalAttribute(annos);
1229  if (!parseResult.has_value())
1230  annos = parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr({});
1231  else if (failed(*parseResult))
1232  return failure();
1233  portAnnotations.push_back(annos);
1234 
1235  // Parse the optional port location.
1236  std::optional<Location> maybeLoc;
1237  if (failed(parser.parseOptionalLocationSpecifier(maybeLoc)))
1238  return failure();
1239  Location loc = maybeLoc ? *maybeLoc : parser.getEncodedSourceLoc(irLoc);
1240  portLocs.push_back(loc);
1241  if (hasSSAIdentifiers)
1242  entryArgs.back().sourceLoc = loc;
1243 
1244  return success();
1245  };
1246 
1247  // Parse all ports.
1248  return parser.parseCommaSeparatedList(OpAsmParser::Delimiter::Paren,
1249  parseArgument);
1250 }

1252 /// Print a paramter list for a module or instance.
1253 static void printParameterList(OpAsmPrinter &p, Operation *op,
1254  ArrayAttr parameters) {
1255  if (!parameters || parameters.empty())
1256  return;
1257 
1258  p << '<';
1259  llvm::interleaveComma(parameters, p, [&](Attribute param) {
1260  auto paramAttr = cast<ParamDeclAttr>(param);
1261  p << paramAttr.getName().getValue() << ": " << paramAttr.getType();
1262  if (auto value = paramAttr.getValue()) {
1263  p << " = ";
1264  p.printAttributeWithoutType(value);
1265  }
1266  });
1267  p << '>';
1268 }

1270 static void printFModuleLikeOp(OpAsmPrinter &p, FModuleLike op) {
1271  p << " ";
1272 
1273  // Print the visibility of the module.
1274  StringRef visibilityAttrName = SymbolTable::getVisibilityAttrName();
1275  if (auto visibility = op->getAttrOfType<StringAttr>(visibilityAttrName))
1276  p << visibility.getValue() << ' ';
1277 
1278  // Print the operation and the function name.
1279  p.printSymbolName(op.getModuleName());
1280 
1281  // Print the parameter list (if non-empty).
1282  printParameterList(p, op, op->getAttrOfType<ArrayAttr>("parameters"));
1283 
1284  // Both modules and external modules have a body, but it is always empty for
1285  // external modules.
1286  Block *body = nullptr;
1287  if (!op->getRegion(0).empty())
1288  body = &op->getRegion(0).front();
1289 
1290  auto needPortNamesAttr = printModulePorts(
1291  p, body, op.getPortDirectionsAttr(), op.getPortNames(), op.getPortTypes(),
1292  op.getPortAnnotations(), op.getPortSymbols(), op.getPortLocations());
1293 
1294  SmallVector<StringRef, 12> omittedAttrs = {
1295  "sym_name", "portDirections", "portTypes", "portAnnotations",
1296  "portSyms", "portLocations", "parameters", visibilityAttrName};
1297 
1298  if (op.getConvention() == Convention::Internal)
1299  omittedAttrs.push_back("convention");
1300 
1301  // We can omit the portNames if they were able to be printed as properly as
1302  // block arguments.
1303  if (!needPortNamesAttr)
1304  omittedAttrs.push_back("portNames");
1305 
1306  // If there are no annotations we can omit the empty array.
1307  if (op->getAttrOfType<ArrayAttr>("annotations").empty())
1308  omittedAttrs.push_back("annotations");
1309 
1310  // If there are no enabled layers, then omit the empty array.
1311  if (auto layers = op->getAttrOfType<ArrayAttr>("layers"))
1312  if (layers.empty())
1313  omittedAttrs.push_back("layers");
1314 
1315  p.printOptionalAttrDictWithKeyword(op->getAttrs(), omittedAttrs);
1316 }

1338 /// Parse an parameter list if present.
1339 /// module-parameter-list ::= `<` parameter-decl (`,` parameter-decl)* `>`
1340 /// parameter-decl ::= identifier `:` type
1341 /// parameter-decl ::= identifier `:` type `=` attribute
1342 ///
1343 static ParseResult
1344 parseOptionalParameters(OpAsmParser &parser,
1345  SmallVectorImpl<Attribute> &parameters) {
1346 
1347  return parser.parseCommaSeparatedList(
1348  OpAsmParser::Delimiter::OptionalLessGreater, [&]() {
1349  std::string name;
1350  Type type;
1351  Attribute value;
1352 
1353  if (parser.parseKeywordOrString(&name) || parser.parseColonType(type))
1354  return failure();
1355 
1356  // Parse the default value if present.
1357  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalEqual())) {
1358  if (parser.parseAttribute(value, type))
1359  return failure();
1360  }
1361 
1362  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
1363  parameters.push_back(ParamDeclAttr::get(
1364  builder.getContext(), builder.getStringAttr(name), type, value));
1365  return success();
1366  });
1367 }

1369 /// Shim to use with assemblyFormat, custom<ParameterList>.
1370 static ParseResult parseParameterList(OpAsmParser &parser,
1371  ArrayAttr &parameters) {

1374  return failure();
1375 
1376  parameters = ArrayAttr::get(parser.getContext(), parseParameters);
1377

1381 static ParseResult parseFModuleLikeOp(OpAsmParser &parser,
1382  OperationState &result,
1383  bool hasSSAIdentifiers) {
1384  auto *context = result.getContext();
1385  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
1386 
1387  // Parse the visibility attribute.
1388  (void)mlir::impl::parseOptionalVisibilityKeyword(parser, result.attributes);
1389 
1390  // Parse the name as a symbol.
1391  StringAttr nameAttr;
1392  if (parser.parseSymbolName(nameAttr, ::mlir::SymbolTable::getSymbolAttrName(),
1393  result.attributes))
1394  return failure();
1395 
1396  // Parse optional parameters.
1397  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> parameters;
1398  if (parseOptionalParameters(parser, parameters))
1399  return failure();
1400  result.addAttribute("parameters", builder.getArrayAttr(parameters));
1401 
1402  // Parse the module ports.
1403  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::Argument> entryArgs;
1404  SmallVector<Direction, 4> portDirections;
1405  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portNames;
1406  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portTypes;
1407  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portAnnotations;
1408  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portSyms;
1409  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portLocs;
1410  if (parseModulePorts(parser, hasSSAIdentifiers, /*supportsSymbols=*/true,
1411  entryArgs, portDirections, portNames, portTypes,
1412  portAnnotations, portSyms, portLocs))
1413  return failure();
1414 
1415  // If module attributes are present, parse them.
1416  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDictWithKeyword(result.attributes))
1417  return failure();
1418 
1419  assert(portNames.size() == portTypes.size());
1420 
1421  // Record the argument and result types as an attribute. This is necessary
1422  // for external modules.
1423 
1424  // Add port directions.
1425  if (!result.attributes.get("portDirections"))
1426  result.addAttribute("portDirections",
1427  direction::packAttribute(context, portDirections));
1428 
1429  // Add port names.
1430  if (!result.attributes.get("portNames"))
1431  result.addAttribute("portNames", builder.getArrayAttr(portNames));
1432 
1433  // Add the port types.
1434  if (!result.attributes.get("portTypes"))
1435  result.addAttribute("portTypes", ArrayAttr::get(context, portTypes));
1436 
1437  // Add the port annotations.
1438  if (!result.attributes.get("portAnnotations")) {
1439  // If there are no portAnnotations, don't add the attribute.
1440  if (llvm::any_of(portAnnotations, [&](Attribute anno) {
1441  return !cast<ArrayAttr>(anno).empty();
1442  }))
1443  result.addAttribute("portAnnotations",
1444  ArrayAttr::get(context, portAnnotations));
1445  }
1446 
1447  // Add port symbols.
1448  if (!result.attributes.get("portSyms")) {
1449  FModuleLike::fixupPortSymsArray(portSyms, builder.getContext());
1450  result.addAttribute("portSyms", builder.getArrayAttr(portSyms));
1451  }
1452 
1453  // Add port locations.
1454  if (!result.attributes.get("portLocations"))
1455  result.addAttribute("portLocations", ArrayAttr::get(context, portLocs));
1456 
1457  // The annotations attribute is always present, but not printed when empty.
1458  if (!result.attributes.get("annotations"))
1459  result.addAttribute("annotations", builder.getArrayAttr({}));
1460 
1461  // The portAnnotations attribute is always present, but not printed when
1462  // empty.
1463  if (!result.attributes.get("portAnnotations"))
1464  result.addAttribute("portAnnotations", builder.getArrayAttr({}));
1465 
1466  // Parse the optional function body.
1467  auto *body = result.addRegion();
1468 
1469  if (hasSSAIdentifiers) {
1470  if (parser.parseRegion(*body, entryArgs))
1471  return failure();
1472  if (body->empty())
1473  body->push_back(new Block());
1474  }
1475  return success();
1476 }

1484  ConventionAttr::get(result.getContext(), Convention::Internal));

1508 LogicalResult FModuleOp::verify() {
1509  // Verify the block arguments.
1510  auto *body = getBodyBlock();
1511  auto portTypes = getPortTypes();
1512  auto portLocs = getPortLocations();
1513  auto numPorts = portTypes.size();
1514 
1515  // Verify that we have the correct number of block arguments.
1516  if (body->getNumArguments() != numPorts)
1517  return emitOpError("entry block must have ")
1518  << numPorts << " arguments to match module signature";
1519 
1520  // Verify the block arguments' types and locations match our attributes.
1521  for (auto [arg, type, loc] : zip(body->getArguments(), portTypes, portLocs)) {
1522  if (arg.getType() != cast<TypeAttr>(type).getValue())
1523  return emitOpError("block argument types should match signature types");
1524  if (arg.getLoc() != cast<LocationAttr>(loc))
1525  return emitOpError(
1526  "block argument locations should match signature locations");
1527  }
1528 
1529  return success();
1530 }

1532 static LogicalResult
1533 verifyInternalPaths(FModuleLike op,
1534  std::optional<::mlir::ArrayAttr> internalPaths) {
1535  if (!internalPaths)
1536  return success();
1537 
1538  // If internal paths are present, should cover all ports.
1539  if (internalPaths->size() != op.getNumPorts())
1540  return op.emitError("module has inconsistent internal path array with ")
1541  << internalPaths->size() << " entries for " << op.getNumPorts()
1542  << " ports";
1543 
1544  // No internal paths for non-ref-type ports.
1545  for (auto [idx, path, typeattr] : llvm::enumerate(
1546  internalPaths->getAsRange<InternalPathAttr>(), op.getPortTypes())) {
1547  if (path.getPath() &&
1548  !type_isa<RefType>(cast<TypeAttr>(typeattr).getValue())) {
1549  auto diag =
1550  op.emitError("module has internal path for non-ref-type port ")
1551  << op.getPortNameAttr(idx);
1552  return diag.attachNote(op.getPortLocation(idx)) << "this port";
1553  }
1554  }
1555 
1556  return success();
1557 }

1559 LogicalResult FExtModuleOp::verify() {
1560  if (failed(verifyInternalPaths(*this, getInternalPaths())))
1561  return failure();
1562 
1563  auto params = getParameters();
1564  if (params.empty())
1565  return success();
1566 
1567  auto checkParmValue = [&](Attribute elt) -> bool {
1568  auto param = cast<ParamDeclAttr>(elt);
1569  auto value = param.getValue();
1570  if (isa<IntegerAttr, StringAttr, FloatAttr, hw::ParamVerbatimAttr>(value))
1571  return true;
1572  emitError() << "has unknown extmodule parameter value '"
1573  << param.getName().getValue() << "' = " << value;
1574  return false;
1575  };
1576 
1577  if (!llvm::all_of(params, checkParmValue))
1578  return failure();
1579 
1580  return success();
1581 }

1607 static LogicalResult verifyProbeType(RefType refType, Location loc,
1608  CircuitOp circuitOp,
1609  SymbolTableCollection &symbolTable,
1610  Twine start) {
1611  auto layer = refType.getLayer();
1612  if (!layer)
1613  return success();
1614  auto *layerOp = symbolTable.lookupSymbolIn(circuitOp, layer);
1615  if (!layerOp)
1616  return emitError(loc) << start << " associated with layer '" << layer
1617  << "', but this layer was not defined";
1618  if (!isa<LayerOp>(layerOp)) {
1619  auto diag = emitError(loc)
1620  << start << " associated with layer '" << layer
1621  << "', but symbol '" << layer << "' does not refer to a '"
1622  << LayerOp::getOperationName() << "' op";
1623  return diag.attachNote(layerOp->getLoc()) << "symbol refers to this op";
1624  }
1625  return success();
1626 }

1628 static LogicalResult verifyPortSymbolUses(FModuleLike module,
1629  SymbolTableCollection &symbolTable) {
1630  // verify types in ports.
1631  auto circuitOp = module->getParentOfType<CircuitOp>();
1632  for (size_t i = 0, e = module.getNumPorts(); i < e; ++i) {
1633  auto type = module.getPortType(i);
1634 
1635  if (auto refType = type_dyn_cast<RefType>(type)) {
1636  if (failed(verifyProbeType(
1637  refType, module.getPortLocation(i), circuitOp, symbolTable,
1638  Twine("probe port '") + module.getPortName(i) + "' is")))
1639  return failure();
1640  continue;
1641  }
1642 
1643  if (auto classType = dyn_cast<ClassType>(type)) {
1644  auto className = classType.getNameAttr();
1645  auto classOp = dyn_cast_or_null<ClassLike>(
1646  symbolTable.lookupSymbolIn(circuitOp, className));
1647  if (!classOp)
1648  return module.emitOpError() << "references unknown class " << className;
1649 
1650  // verify that the result type agrees with the class definition.
1651  if (failed(classOp.verifyType(classType,
1652  [&]() { return module.emitOpError(); })))
1653  return failure();
1654  continue;
1655  }
1656  }
1657 
1658  return success();
1659 }

1661 LogicalResult FModuleOp::verifySymbolUses(SymbolTableCollection &symbolTable) {

1663  verifyPortSymbolUses(cast<FModuleLike>(getOperation()), symbolTable)))

1665 
1666  auto circuitOp = (*this)->getParentOfType<CircuitOp>();
1667  for (auto layer : getLayers()) {

1669  return emitOpError() << "enables unknown layer '" << layer << "'";

1673 }

1730 LogicalResult firrtl::detail::verifyTypeAgainstClassLike(
1731  ClassLike classOp, ClassType type,
1732  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError) {
1733  // This check is probably not required, but done for sanity.
1734  auto name = type.getNameAttr().getAttr();
1735  auto expectedName = classOp.getModuleNameAttr();
1736  if (name != expectedName)
1737  return emitError() << "type has wrong name, got " << name << ", expected "
1738  << expectedName;
1739 
1740  auto elements = type.getElements();
1741  auto numElements = elements.size();
1742  auto expectedNumElements = classOp.getNumPorts();
1743  if (numElements != expectedNumElements)
1744  return emitError() << "has wrong number of ports, got " << numElements
1745  << ", expected " << expectedNumElements;
1746 
1747  auto portNames = classOp.getPortNames();
1748  auto portDirections = classOp.getPortDirections();
1749  auto portTypes = classOp.getPortTypes();
1750 
1751  for (unsigned i = 0; i < numElements; ++i) {
1752  auto element = elements[i];
1753 
1754  auto name = element.name;
1755  auto expectedName = portNames[i];
1756  if (name != expectedName)
1757  return emitError() << "port #" << i << " has wrong name, got " << name
1758  << ", expected " << expectedName;
1759 
1760  auto direction = element.direction;
1761  auto expectedDirection = Direction(portDirections[i]);
1762  if (direction != expectedDirection)
1763  return emitError() << "port " << name << " has wrong direction, got "
1764  << direction::toString(direction) << ", expected "
1765  << direction::toString(expectedDirection);
1766 
1767  auto type = element.type;
1768  auto expectedType = cast<TypeAttr>(portTypes[i]).getValue();
1769  if (type != expectedType)
1770  return emitError() << "port " << name << " has wrong type, got " << type
1771  << ", expected " << expectedType;
1772  }
1773 
1774  return success();
1775 }

1777 ClassType firrtl::detail::getInstanceTypeForClassLike(ClassLike classOp) {
1778  auto n = classOp.getNumPorts();
1779  SmallVector<ClassElement> elements;
1780  elements.reserve(n);
1781  for (size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i)
1782  elements.push_back({classOp.getPortNameAttr(i), classOp.getPortType(i),
1783  classOp.getPortDirection(i)});
1784  auto name = FlatSymbolRefAttr::get(classOp.getNameAttr());
1785  return ClassType::get(name, elements);
1786 }

1788 static ParseResult parseClassLike(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result,
1789  bool hasSSAIdentifiers) {
1790  auto *context = result.getContext();
1791  auto &builder = parser.getBuilder();
1792 
1793  // Parse the visibility attribute.
1794  (void)mlir::impl::parseOptionalVisibilityKeyword(parser, result.attributes);
1795 
1796  // Parse the name as a symbol.
1797  StringAttr nameAttr;
1798  if (parser.parseSymbolName(nameAttr, ::mlir::SymbolTable::getSymbolAttrName(),
1799  result.attributes))
1800  return failure();
1801 
1802  // Parse the module ports.
1803  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::Argument> entryArgs;
1804  SmallVector<Direction, 4> portDirections;
1805  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portNames;
1806  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portTypes;
1807  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portAnnotations;
1808  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portSyms;
1809  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portLocs;
1810  if (parseModulePorts(parser, hasSSAIdentifiers,
1811  /*supportsSymbols=*/false, entryArgs, portDirections,
1812  portNames, portTypes, portAnnotations, portSyms,
1813  portLocs))
1814  return failure();
1815 
1816  // Ports on ClassLike ops cannot have annotations
1817  for (auto annos : portAnnotations)
1818  if (!cast<ArrayAttr>(annos).empty())
1819  return failure();
1820 
1821  // If attributes are present, parse them.
1822  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDictWithKeyword(result.attributes))
1823  return failure();
1824 
1825  assert(portNames.size() == portTypes.size());
1826 
1827  // Record the argument and result types as an attribute. This is necessary
1828  // for external modules.
1829 
1830  // Add port directions.
1831  if (!result.attributes.get("portDirections"))
1832  result.addAttribute("portDirections",
1833  direction::packAttribute(context, portDirections));
1834 
1835  // Add port names.
1836  if (!result.attributes.get("portNames"))
1837  result.addAttribute("portNames", builder.getArrayAttr(portNames));
1838 
1839  // Add the port types.
1840  if (!result.attributes.get("portTypes"))
1841  result.addAttribute("portTypes", builder.getArrayAttr(portTypes));
1842 
1843  // Add the port symbols.
1844  if (!result.attributes.get("portSyms")) {
1845  FModuleLike::fixupPortSymsArray(portSyms, builder.getContext());
1846  result.addAttribute("portSyms", builder.getArrayAttr(portSyms));
1847  }
1848 
1849  // Add port locations.
1850  if (!result.attributes.get("portLocations"))
1851  result.addAttribute("portLocations", ArrayAttr::get(context, portLocs));
1852 
1853  // Notably missing compared to other FModuleLike, we do not track port
1854  // annotations, nor port symbols, on classes.
1855 
1856  // Add the region (unused by extclass).
1857  auto *bodyRegion = result.addRegion();
1858 
1859  if (hasSSAIdentifiers) {
1860  if (parser.parseRegion(*bodyRegion, entryArgs))
1861  return failure();
1862  if (bodyRegion->empty())
1863  bodyRegion->push_back(new Block());
1864  }
1865 
1866  return success();
1867 }
1868 
1869 static void printClassLike(OpAsmPrinter &p, ClassLike op) {
1870  p << ' ';
1871 
1872  // Print the visibility of the class.
1873  StringRef visibilityAttrName = SymbolTable::getVisibilityAttrName();
1874  if (auto visibility = op->getAttrOfType<StringAttr>(visibilityAttrName))
1875  p << visibility.getValue() << ' ';
1876 
1877  // Print the class name.
1878  p.printSymbolName(op.getName());
1879 
1880  // Both classes and external classes have a body, but it is always empty for
1881  // external classes.
1882  Region &region = op->getRegion(0);
1883  Block *body = nullptr;
1884  if (!region.empty())
1885  body = &region.front();
1886 
1887  auto needPortNamesAttr = printModulePorts(
1888  p, body, op.getPortDirectionsAttr(), op.getPortNames(), op.getPortTypes(),
1889  {}, op.getPortSymbols(), op.getPortLocations());
1890 
1891  // Print the attr-dict.
1892  SmallVector<StringRef, 8> omittedAttrs = {
1893  "sym_name", "portNames", "portTypes", "portDirections",
1894  "portSyms", "portLocations", visibilityAttrName};
1895 
1896  // We can omit the portNames if they were able to be printed as properly as
1897  // block arguments.
1898  if (!needPortNamesAttr)
1899  omittedAttrs.push_back("portNames");
1900 
1901  p.printOptionalAttrDictWithKeyword(op->getAttrs(), omittedAttrs);
1902 
1903  // print the body if it exists.
1904  if (!region.empty()) {
1905  p << " ";
1906  auto printEntryBlockArgs = false;
1907  auto printBlockTerminators = false;
1908  p.printRegion(region, printEntryBlockArgs, printBlockTerminators);
1909  }
1910 }

2206 LogicalResult InstanceOp::verify() {
2207  // The instance may only be instantiated under its required layers.
2208  auto ambientLayers = getAmbientLayersAt(getOperation());
2209  SmallVector<SymbolRefAttr> missingLayers;

2225 /// Builds a new `InstanceOp` with the ports listed in `portIndices` erased, and
2226 /// updates any users of the remaining ports to point at the new instance.
2227 InstanceOp InstanceOp::erasePorts(OpBuilder &builder,
2228  const llvm::BitVector &portIndices) {
2229  assert(portIndices.size() >= getNumResults() &&
2230  "portIndices is not at least as large as getNumResults()");
2231 
2232  if (portIndices.none())
2233  return *this;
2234 
2235  SmallVector<Type> newResultTypes = removeElementsAtIndices<Type>(
2236  SmallVector<Type>(result_type_begin(), result_type_end()), portIndices);
2237  SmallVector<Direction> newPortDirections = removeElementsAtIndices<Direction>(
2238  direction::unpackAttribute(getPortDirectionsAttr()), portIndices);
2239  SmallVector<Attribute> newPortNames =
2240  removeElementsAtIndices(getPortNames().getValue(), portIndices);
2241  SmallVector<Attribute> newPortAnnotations =
2242  removeElementsAtIndices(getPortAnnotations().getValue(), portIndices);
2243 
2244  auto newOp = builder.create<InstanceOp>(
2245  getLoc(), newResultTypes, getModuleName(), getName(), getNameKind(),
2246  newPortDirections, newPortNames, getAnnotations().getValue(),
2247  newPortAnnotations, getLayers(), getLowerToBind(), getInnerSymAttr());
2248 
2249  for (unsigned oldIdx = 0, newIdx = 0, numOldPorts = getNumResults();
2250  oldIdx != numOldPorts; ++oldIdx) {
2251  if (portIndices.test(oldIdx)) {
2252  assert(getResult(oldIdx).use_empty() && "removed instance port has uses");
2253  continue;
2254  }
2255  getResult(oldIdx).replaceAllUsesWith(newOp.getResult(newIdx));
2256  ++newIdx;
2257  }
2258 
2259  // Compy over "output_file" information so that this is not lost when ports
2260  // are erased.
2261  //
2262  // TODO: Other attributes may need to be copied over.
2263  if (auto outputFile = (*this)->getAttr("output_file"))
2264  newOp->setAttr("output_file", outputFile);
2265 
2266  return newOp;
2267 }

2282 InstanceOp
2283 InstanceOp::cloneAndInsertPorts(ArrayRef<std::pair<unsigned, PortInfo>> ports) {
2284  auto portSize = ports.size();
2285  auto newPortCount = getNumResults() + portSize;
2286  SmallVector<Direction> newPortDirections;
2287  newPortDirections.reserve(newPortCount);
2288  SmallVector<Attribute> newPortNames;
2289  newPortNames.reserve(newPortCount);
2290  SmallVector<Type> newPortTypes;
2291  newPortTypes.reserve(newPortCount);
2292  SmallVector<Attribute> newPortAnnos;
2293  newPortAnnos.reserve(newPortCount);
2294 
2295  unsigned oldIndex = 0;
2296  unsigned newIndex = 0;
2297  while (oldIndex + newIndex < newPortCount) {
2298  // Check if we should insert a port here.
2299  if (newIndex < portSize && ports[newIndex].first == oldIndex) {
2300  auto &newPort = ports[newIndex].second;
2301  newPortDirections.push_back(newPort.direction);
2302  newPortNames.push_back(newPort.name);
2303  newPortTypes.push_back(newPort.type);
2304  newPortAnnos.push_back(newPort.annotations.getArrayAttr());
2305  ++newIndex;
2306  } else {
2307  // Copy the next old port.
2308  newPortDirections.push_back(getPortDirection(oldIndex));
2309  newPortNames.push_back(getPortName(oldIndex));
2310  newPortTypes.push_back(getType(oldIndex));
2311  newPortAnnos.push_back(getPortAnnotation(oldIndex));
2312  ++oldIndex;
2313  }
2314  }
2315 
2316  // Create a new instance op with the reset inserted.
2317  return OpBuilder(*this).create<InstanceOp>(
2318  getLoc(), newPortTypes, getModuleName(), getName(), getNameKind(),
2319  newPortDirections, newPortNames, getAnnotations().getValue(),
2320  newPortAnnos, getLayers(), getLowerToBind(), getInnerSymAttr());
2321 }

2368 ParseResult InstanceOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
2369  auto *context = parser.getContext();
2370  auto &resultAttrs = result.attributes;
2371 
2372  std::string name;
2373  hw::InnerSymAttr innerSymAttr;
2374  FlatSymbolRefAttr moduleName;
2375  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::Argument> entryArgs;
2376  SmallVector<Direction, 4> portDirections;
2377  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portNames;
2378  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portTypes;
2379  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portAnnotations;
2380  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portSyms;
2381  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portLocs;
2382  NameKindEnumAttr nameKind;
2383 
2384  if (parser.parseKeywordOrString(&name))
2385  return failure();
2386  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("sym"))) {
2387  if (parser.parseCustomAttributeWithFallback(
2388  innerSymAttr, ::mlir::Type{},
2389  hw::InnerSymbolTable::getInnerSymbolAttrName(),
2390  result.attributes)) {
2391  return ::mlir::failure();
2392  }
2393  }
2394  if (parseNameKind(parser, nameKind) ||
2395  parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
2396  parser.parseAttribute(moduleName, "moduleName", resultAttrs) ||
2397  parseModulePorts(parser, /*hasSSAIdentifiers=*/false,
2398  /*supportsSymbols=*/false, entryArgs, portDirections,
2399  portNames, portTypes, portAnnotations, portSyms,
2400  portLocs))
2401  return failure();
2402 
2403  // Add the attributes. We let attributes defined in the attr-dict override
2404  // attributes parsed out of the module signature.
2405  if (!resultAttrs.get("moduleName"))
2406  result.addAttribute("moduleName", moduleName);
2407  if (!resultAttrs.get("name"))
2408  result.addAttribute("name", StringAttr::get(context, name));
2409  result.addAttribute("nameKind", nameKind);
2410  if (!resultAttrs.get("portDirections"))
2411  result.addAttribute("portDirections",
2412  direction::packAttribute(context, portDirections));

2420  // if they are empty, empty, and false (respectively).

2454 void InstanceChoiceOp::build(
2455  OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result, FModuleLike defaultModule,
2456  ArrayRef<std::pair<OptionCaseOp, FModuleLike>> cases, StringRef name,
2457  NameKindEnum nameKind, ArrayRef<Attribute> annotations,
2458  ArrayRef<Attribute> portAnnotations, StringAttr innerSym) {
2459  // Gather the result types.
2460  SmallVector<Type> resultTypes;
2461  for (Attribute portType : defaultModule.getPortTypes())
2462  resultTypes.push_back(cast<TypeAttr>(portType).getValue());
2463 
2464  // Create the port annotations.
2465  ArrayAttr portAnnotationsAttr;
2466  if (portAnnotations.empty()) {
2467  portAnnotationsAttr = builder.getArrayAttr(SmallVector<Attribute, 16>(
2468  resultTypes.size(), builder.getArrayAttr({})));
2469  } else {
2470  portAnnotationsAttr = builder.getArrayAttr(portAnnotations);
2471  }
2472 
2473  // Gather the module & case names.
2474  SmallVector<Attribute> moduleNames, caseNames;
2475  moduleNames.push_back(SymbolRefAttr::get(defaultModule.getModuleNameAttr()));
2476  for (auto [caseOption, caseModule] : cases) {
2477  auto caseGroup = caseOption->getParentOfType<OptionOp>();
2478  caseNames.push_back(SymbolRefAttr::get(caseGroup.getSymNameAttr(),
2479  {SymbolRefAttr::get(caseOption)}));
2480  moduleNames.push_back(SymbolRefAttr::get(caseModule.getModuleNameAttr()));
2481  }
2482 
2483  return build(builder, result, resultTypes, builder.getArrayAttr(moduleNames),
2484  builder.getArrayAttr(caseNames), builder.getStringAttr(name),
2485  NameKindEnumAttr::get(builder.getContext(), nameKind),
2486  defaultModule.getPortDirectionsAttr(),
2487  defaultModule.getPortNamesAttr(),
2488  builder.getArrayAttr(annotations), portAnnotationsAttr,
2489  defaultModule.getLayersAttr(),
2490  innerSym ? hw::InnerSymAttr::get(innerSym) : hw::InnerSymAttr());

2497 void InstanceChoiceOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
2498  // Print the instance name.
2499  p << " ";
2500  p.printKeywordOrString(getName());
2501  if (auto attr = getInnerSymAttr()) {
2502  p << " sym ";
2503  p.printSymbolName(attr.getSymName());
2504  }
2505  if (getNameKindAttr().getValue() != NameKindEnum::DroppableName)
2506  p << ' ' << stringifyNameKindEnum(getNameKindAttr().getValue());
2507 
2508  // Print the attr-dict.
2509  SmallVector<StringRef, 10> omittedAttrs = {
2510  "moduleNames", "caseNames", "name",
2511  "portDirections", "portNames", "portTypes",
2512  "portAnnotations", "inner_sym", "nameKind"};
2513  if (getAnnotations().empty())
2514  omittedAttrs.push_back("annotations");
2515  if (getLayers().empty())
2516  omittedAttrs.push_back("layers");
2517  p.printOptionalAttrDict((*this)->getAttrs(), omittedAttrs);
2518 
2519  // Print the module name.
2520  p << ' ';
2521 
2522  auto moduleNames = getModuleNamesAttr();
2523  auto caseNames = getCaseNamesAttr();
2524 
2525  p.printSymbolName(moduleNames[0].cast<FlatSymbolRefAttr>().getValue());
2526 
2527  p << " alternatives ";
2528  p.printSymbolName(
2529  caseNames[0].cast<SymbolRefAttr>().getRootReference().getValue());
2530  p << " { ";
2531  for (size_t i = 0, n = caseNames.size(); i < n; ++i) {
2532  if (i != 0)
2533  p << ", ";
2534 
2535  auto symbol = caseNames[i].cast<SymbolRefAttr>();
2536  p.printSymbolName(symbol.getNestedReferences()[0].getValue());
2537  p << " -> ";
2538  p.printSymbolName(moduleNames[i + 1].cast<FlatSymbolRefAttr>().getValue());
2539  }
2540 
2541  p << " } ";
2542 
2543  // Collect all the result types as TypeAttrs for printing.
2544  SmallVector<Attribute> portTypes;
2545  portTypes.reserve(getNumResults());
2546  llvm::transform(getResultTypes(), std::back_inserter(portTypes),
2547  &TypeAttr::get);
2548  printModulePorts(p, /*block=*/nullptr, getPortDirectionsAttr(),
2549  getPortNames().getValue(), portTypes,
2550  getPortAnnotations().getValue(), {}, {});
2551 }

2553 ParseResult InstanceChoiceOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser,
2554  OperationState &result) {
2555  auto *context = parser.getContext();
2556  auto &resultAttrs = result.attributes;
2557 
2558  std::string name;
2559  hw::InnerSymAttr innerSymAttr;
2560  SmallVector<Attribute> moduleNames;
2561  SmallVector<Attribute> caseNames;
2562  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::Argument> entryArgs;
2563  SmallVector<Direction, 4> portDirections;
2564  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portNames;
2565  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portTypes;
2566  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portAnnotations;
2567  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portSyms;
2568  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> portLocs;
2569  NameKindEnumAttr nameKind;
2570 
2571  if (parser.parseKeywordOrString(&name))
2572  return failure();
2573  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("sym"))) {
2574  if (parser.parseCustomAttributeWithFallback(
2575  innerSymAttr, Type{},
2576  hw::InnerSymbolTable::getInnerSymbolAttrName(),
2577  result.attributes)) {
2578  return failure();
2579  }
2580  }
2581  if (parseNameKind(parser, nameKind) ||
2582  parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes))
2583  return failure();
2584 
2585  FlatSymbolRefAttr defaultModuleName;
2586  if (parser.parseAttribute(defaultModuleName))
2587  return failure();
2588  moduleNames.push_back(defaultModuleName);
2589 
2590  // alternatives { @opt::@case -> @target, ... }
2591  {
2592  FlatSymbolRefAttr optionName;
2593  if (parser.parseKeyword("alternatives") ||
2594  parser.parseAttribute(optionName) || parser.parseLBrace())
2595  return failure();
2596 
2597  FlatSymbolRefAttr moduleName;
2598  StringAttr caseName;
2599  while (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalSymbolName(caseName))) {
2600  if (parser.parseArrow() || parser.parseAttribute(moduleName))
2601  return failure();
2602  moduleNames.push_back(moduleName);
2603  caseNames.push_back(SymbolRefAttr::get(
2604  optionName.getAttr(), {FlatSymbolRefAttr::get(caseName)}));
2605  if (failed(parser.parseOptionalComma()))
2606  break;
2607  }
2608  if (parser.parseRBrace())
2609  return failure();
2610  }
2611 
2612  if (parseModulePorts(parser, /*hasSSAIdentifiers=*/false,
2613  /*supportsSymbols=*/false, entryArgs, portDirections,
2614  portNames, portTypes, portAnnotations, portSyms,
2615  portLocs))
2616  return failure();
2617 
2618  // Add the attributes. We let attributes defined in the attr-dict override
2619  // attributes parsed out of the module signature.
2620  if (!resultAttrs.get("moduleNames"))
2621  result.addAttribute("moduleNames", ArrayAttr::get(context, moduleNames));
2622  if (!resultAttrs.get("caseNames"))
2623  result.addAttribute("caseNames", ArrayAttr::get(context, caseNames));
2624  if (!resultAttrs.get("name"))
2625  result.addAttribute("name", StringAttr::get(context, name));
2626  result.addAttribute("nameKind", nameKind);
2627  if (!resultAttrs.get("portDirections"))
2628  result.addAttribute("portDirections",
2629  direction::packAttribute(context, portDirections));
2630  if (!resultAttrs.get("portNames"))
2631  result.addAttribute("portNames", ArrayAttr::get(context, portNames));
2632  if (!resultAttrs.get("portAnnotations"))
2633  result.addAttribute("portAnnotations",
2634  ArrayAttr::get(context, portAnnotations));
2635 
2636  // Annotations, layers, and LowerToBind are omitted in the printed format if
2637  // they are empty, empty, and false (respectively).
2638  if (!resultAttrs.get("annotations"))
2639  resultAttrs.append("annotations", parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr({}));
2640  if (!resultAttrs.get("layers"))
2641  resultAttrs.append("layers", parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr({}));
2642 
2643  // Add result types.
2644  result.types.reserve(portTypes.size());
2645  llvm::transform(
2646  portTypes, std::back_inserter(result.types),
2647  [](Attribute typeAttr) { return cast<TypeAttr>(typeAttr).getValue(); });
2648 
2649  return success();
2650 }

2658 LogicalResult InstanceChoiceOp::verify() {
2659  if (getCaseNamesAttr().empty())
2660  return emitOpError() << "must have at least one case";
2661  if (getModuleNamesAttr().size() != getCaseNamesAttr().size() + 1)
2662  return emitOpError() << "number of referenced modules does not match the "
2663  "number of options";
2664 
2665  // The modules may only be instantiated under their required layers (which
2666  // are the same for all modules).
2667  auto ambientLayers = getAmbientLayersAt(getOperation());
2668  SmallVector<SymbolRefAttr> missingLayers;
2669  for (auto layer : getLayersAttr().getAsRange<SymbolRefAttr>())
2670  if (!isLayerCompatibleWith(layer, ambientLayers))
2671  missingLayers.push_back(layer);
2672 
2673  if (missingLayers.empty())
2674  return success();
2675 
2676  auto diag =
2677  emitOpError("ambient layers are insufficient to instantiate module");
2678  auto &note = diag.attachNote();
2679  note << "missing layer requirements: ";
2680  interleaveComma(missingLayers, note);
2681  return failure();
2682 }

2684 LogicalResult
2685 InstanceChoiceOp::verifySymbolUses(SymbolTableCollection &symbolTable) {
2686  auto caseNames = getCaseNamesAttr();
2687  for (auto moduleName : getModuleNamesAttr()) {
2688  if (failed(instance_like_impl::verifyReferencedModule(
2689  *this, symbolTable, moduleName.cast<FlatSymbolRefAttr>())))
2690  return failure();
2691  }
2692 
2693  auto root = caseNames[0].cast<SymbolRefAttr>().getRootReference();
2694  for (size_t i = 0, n = caseNames.size(); i < n; ++i) {
2695  auto ref = caseNames[i].cast<SymbolRefAttr>();
2696  auto refRoot = ref.getRootReference();
2697  if (ref.getRootReference() != root)
2698  return emitOpError() << "case " << ref
2699  << " is not in the same option group as "
2700  << caseNames[0];
2701 
2702  if (!symbolTable.lookupNearestSymbolFrom<OptionOp>(*this, refRoot))
2703  return emitOpError() << "option " << refRoot << " does not exist";
2704 
2705  if (!symbolTable.lookupNearestSymbolFrom<OptionCaseOp>(*this, ref))
2706  return emitOpError() << "option " << refRoot
2707  << " does not contain option case " << ref;
2708  }
2709 
2710  return success();
2711 }

2803 void MemOp::getNumPorts(size_t &numReadPorts, size_t &numWritePorts,
2804  size_t &numReadWritePorts, size_t &numDbgsPorts) {

2822 /// Verify the correctness of a MemOp.
2823 LogicalResult MemOp::verify() {
2824 
2825  // Store the port names as we find them. This lets us check quickly
2826  // for uniqueneess.
2827  llvm::SmallDenseSet<Attribute, 8> portNamesSet;
2828 
2829  // Store the previous data type. This lets us check that the data
2830  // type is consistent across all ports.
2831  FIRRTLType oldDataType;
2832 
2833  for (size_t i = 0, e = getNumResults(); i != e; ++i) {
2834  auto portName = getPortName(i);
2835 
2836  // Get a bundle type representing this port, stripping an outer
2837  // flip if it exists. If this is not a bundle<> or
2838  // flip<bundle<>>, then this is an error.
2839  BundleType portBundleType =
2840  type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(getResult(i).getType());
2841 
2842  // Require that all port names are unique.
2843  if (!portNamesSet.insert(portName).second) {
2844  emitOpError() << "has non-unique port name " << portName;
2845  return failure();
2846  }
2847 
2848  // Determine the kind of the memory. If the kind cannot be
2849  // determined, then it's indicative of the wrong number of fields
2850  // in the type (but we don't know any more just yet).
2851 
2852  auto elt = getPortNamed(portName);
2853  if (!elt) {
2854  emitOpError() << "could not get port with name " << portName;
2855  return failure();
2856  }
2857  auto firrtlType = type_cast<FIRRTLType>(elt.getType());
2858  MemOp::PortKind portKind = getMemPortKindFromType(firrtlType);
2859 
2860  if (portKind == MemOp::PortKind::Debug &&
2861  !type_isa<RefType>(getResult(i).getType()))
2862  return emitOpError() << "has an invalid type on port " << portName
2863  << " (expected Read/Write/ReadWrite/Debug)";
2864  if (type_isa<RefType>(firrtlType) && e == 1)
2865  return emitOpError()
2866  << "cannot have only one port of debug type. Debug port can only "
2867  "exist alongside other read/write/read-write port";
2868 
2869  // Safely search for the "data" field, erroring if it can't be
2870  // found.
2871  FIRRTLBaseType dataType;
2872  if (portKind == MemOp::PortKind::Debug) {
2873  auto resType = type_cast<RefType>(getResult(i).getType());
2874  if (!(resType && type_isa<FVectorType>(resType.getType())))
2875  return emitOpError() << "debug ports must be a RefType of FVectorType";
2876  dataType = type_cast<FVectorType>(resType.getType()).getElementType();
2877  } else {
2878  auto dataTypeOption = portBundleType.getElement("data");
2879  if (!dataTypeOption && portKind == MemOp::PortKind::ReadWrite)
2880  dataTypeOption = portBundleType.getElement("wdata");
2881  if (!dataTypeOption) {
2882  emitOpError() << "has no data field on port " << portName
2883  << " (expected to see \"data\" for a read or write "
2884  "port or \"rdata\" for a read/write port)";
2885  return failure();
2886  }
2887  dataType = dataTypeOption->type;
2888  // Read data is expected to ba a flip.
2889  if (portKind == MemOp::PortKind::Read) {
2890  // FIXME error on missing bundle flip
2891  }
2892  }
2893 
2894  // Error if the data type isn't passive.
2895  if (!dataType.isPassive()) {
2896  emitOpError() << "has non-passive data type on port " << portName
2897  << " (memory types must be passive)";
2898  return failure();
2899  }
2900 
2901  // Error if the data type contains analog types.
2902  if (dataType.containsAnalog()) {
2903  emitOpError() << "has a data type that contains an analog type on port "
2904  << portName
2905  << " (memory types cannot contain analog types)";
2906  return failure();
2907  }
2908 
2909  // Check that the port type matches the kind that we determined
2910  // for this port. This catches situations of extraneous port
2911  // fields beind included or the fields being named incorrectly.
2912  FIRRTLType expectedType =
2913  getTypeForPort(getDepth(), dataType, portKind,
2914  dataType.isGround() ? getMaskBits() : 0);
2915  // Compute the original port type as portBundleType may have
2916  // stripped outer flip information.
2917  auto originalType = getResult(i).getType();
2918  if (originalType != expectedType) {
2919  StringRef portKindName;
2920  switch (portKind) {
2921  case MemOp::PortKind::Read:
2922  portKindName = "read";
2923  break;
2924  case MemOp::PortKind::Write:
2925  portKindName = "write";
2926  break;
2927  case MemOp::PortKind::ReadWrite:
2928  portKindName = "readwrite";
2929  break;
2930  case MemOp::PortKind::Debug:
2931  portKindName = "dbg";
2932  break;
2933  }
2934  emitOpError() << "has an invalid type for port " << portName
2935  << " of determined kind \"" << portKindName
2936  << "\" (expected " << expectedType << ", but got "
2937  << originalType << ")";
2938  return failure();
2939  }
2940 
2941  // Error if the type of the current port was not the same as the
2942  // last port, but skip checking the first port.
2943  if (oldDataType && oldDataType != dataType) {
2944  emitOpError() << "port " << getPortName(i)
2945  << " has a different type than port " << getPortName(i - 1)
2946  << " (expected " << oldDataType << ", but got " << dataType
2947  << ")";
2948  return failure();
2949  }
2950 
2951  oldDataType = dataType;
2952  }
2953 
2954  auto maskWidth = getMaskBits();
2955 
2956  auto dataWidth = getDataType().getBitWidthOrSentinel();
2957  if (dataWidth > 0 && maskWidth > (size_t)dataWidth)
2958  return emitOpError("the mask width cannot be greater than "
2959  "data width");
2960 
2961  if (getPortAnnotations().size() != getNumResults())
2962  return emitOpError("the number of result annotations should be "
2963  "equal to the number of results");
2964 
2965  return success();
2966 }
