2974 FIRRTLType MemOp::getTypeForPort(uint64_t depth, FIRRTLBaseType dataType,
2975  PortKind portKind, size_t maskBits) {
2976 
2977  auto *context = dataType.getContext();
2978  if (portKind == PortKind::Debug)
2979  return RefType::get(FVectorType::get(dataType, depth));
2980  FIRRTLBaseType maskType;
2981  // maskBits not specified (==0), then get the mask type from the dataType.
2982  if (maskBits == 0)
2983  maskType = dataType.getMaskType();
2984  else
2985  maskType = UIntType::get(context, maskBits);
2986 
2987  auto getId = [&](StringRef name) -> StringAttr {
2988  return StringAttr::get(context, name);

3377 /// Check if the source and sink are of appropriate flow.
3378 static LogicalResult checkConnectFlow(Operation *connect) {
3379  Value dst = connect->getOperand(0);
3380  Value src = connect->getOperand(1);
3381 
3382  // TODO: Relax this to allow reads from output ports,
3383  // instance/memory input ports.

3385  if (!isValidSrc(srcFlow)) {
3386  // A sink that is a port output or instance input used as a source is okay.
3387  auto kind = getDeclarationKind(src);
3388  if (kind != DeclKind::Port && kind != DeclKind::Instance) {

3390  auto [srcName, rootKnown] = getFieldName(srcRef);
3391  auto diag = emitError(connect->getLoc());
3392  diag << "connect has invalid flow: the source expression ";

3395  diag << "has " << toString(srcFlow) << ", expected source or duplex flow";
3396  return diag.attachNote(srcRef.getLoc()) << "the source was defined here";
3397  }
3398  }

3400  auto dstFlow = foldFlow(dst);
3401  if (!isValidDst(dstFlow)) {
3402  auto dstRef = getFieldRefFromValue(dst, /*lookThroughCasts=*/true);
3403  auto [dstName, rootKnown] = getFieldName(dstRef);

3406  if (rootKnown)

3416 /// Checks if the type has any 'const' leaf elements . If `isFlip` is `true`,
3417 /// the `const` leaf is not considered to be driven.
3418 static bool isConstFieldDriven(FIRRTLBaseType type, bool isFlip = false,
3419  bool outerTypeIsConst = false) {
3420  auto typeIsConst = outerTypeIsConst || type.isConst();
3421 
3422  if (typeIsConst && type.isPassive())
3423  return !isFlip;
3424 
3425  if (auto bundleType = type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(type))
3426  return llvm::any_of(bundleType.getElements(), [&](auto &element) {
3427  return isConstFieldDriven(element.type, isFlip ^ element.isFlip,
3428  typeIsConst);
3429  });
3430 
3431  if (auto vectorType = type_dyn_cast<FVectorType>(type))
3432  return isConstFieldDriven(vectorType.getElementType(), isFlip, typeIsConst);
3433 
3434  if (typeIsConst)
3435  return !isFlip;
3436  return false;
3437 }

3440 /// Checks that connections to 'const' destinations are not dependent on
3441 /// non-'const' conditions in when blocks.
3442 static LogicalResult checkConnectConditionality(FConnectLike connect) {
3443  auto dest = connect.getDest();
3444  auto destType = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(dest.getType());
3445  auto src = connect.getSrc();
3446  auto srcType = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(src.getType());
3447  if (!destType || !srcType)
3448  return success();
3449 
3450  auto destRefinedType = destType;
3451  auto srcRefinedType = srcType;
3452 
3453  /// Looks up the value's defining op until the defining op is null or a
3454  /// declaration of the value. If a SubAccessOp is encountered with a 'const'
3455  /// input, `originalFieldType` is made 'const'.
3456  auto findFieldDeclarationRefiningFieldType =
3457  [](Value value, FIRRTLBaseType &originalFieldType) -> Value {
3458  while (auto *definingOp = value.getDefiningOp()) {
3459  bool shouldContinue = true;
3460  TypeSwitch<Operation *>(definingOp)
3461  .Case<SubfieldOp, SubindexOp>([&](auto op) { value = op.getInput(); })
3462  .Case<SubaccessOp>([&](SubaccessOp op) {
3463  if (op.getInput()
3464  .getType()
3465  .base()
3466  .getElementTypePreservingConst()
3467  .isConst())
3468  originalFieldType = originalFieldType.getConstType(true);
3469  value = op.getInput();
3470  })
3471  .Default([&](Operation *) { shouldContinue = false; });
3472  if (!shouldContinue)
3473  break;
3474  }
3475  return value;
3476  };
3477 
3478  auto destDeclaration =
3479  findFieldDeclarationRefiningFieldType(dest, destRefinedType);
3480  auto srcDeclaration =
3481  findFieldDeclarationRefiningFieldType(src, srcRefinedType);
3482 
3483  auto checkConstConditionality = [&](Value value, FIRRTLBaseType type,
3484  Value declaration) -> LogicalResult {
3485  auto *declarationBlock = declaration.getParentBlock();
3486  auto *block = connect->getBlock();
3487  while (block && block != declarationBlock) {
3488  auto *parentOp = block->getParentOp();
3489 
3490  if (auto whenOp = dyn_cast<WhenOp>(parentOp);
3491  whenOp && !whenOp.getCondition().getType().isConst()) {
3492  if (type.isConst())
3493  return connect.emitOpError()
3494  << "assignment to 'const' type " << type
3495  << " is dependent on a non-'const' condition";
3496  return connect->emitOpError()
3497  << "assignment to nested 'const' member of type " << type
3498  << " is dependent on a non-'const' condition";
3499  }
3500 
3501  block = parentOp->getBlock();
3502  }
3503  return success();
3504  };
3505 
3506  auto emitSubaccessError = [&] {
3507  return connect.emitError(
3508  "assignment to non-'const' subaccess of 'const' type is disallowed");
3509  };
3510 
3511  // Check destination if it contains 'const' leaves
3512  if (destRefinedType.containsConst() && isConstFieldDriven(destRefinedType)) {
3513  // Disallow assignment to non-'const' subaccesses of 'const' types
3514  if (destType != destRefinedType)
3515  return emitSubaccessError();
3516 
3517  if (failed(checkConstConditionality(dest, destType, destDeclaration)))
3518  return failure();
3519  }
3520 
3521  // Check source if it contains 'const' 'flip' leaves
3522  if (srcRefinedType.containsConst() &&
3523  isConstFieldDriven(srcRefinedType, /*isFlip=*/true)) {
3524  // Disallow assignment to non-'const' subaccesses of 'const' types
3525  if (srcType != srcRefinedType)
3526  return emitSubaccessError();
3527  if (failed(checkConstConditionality(src, srcType, srcDeclaration)))
3528  return failure();
3529  }
3530 
3531  return success();
3532 }

3534 LogicalResult ConnectOp::verify() {
3535  auto dstType = getDest().getType();
3536  auto srcType = getSrc().getType();
3537  auto dstBaseType = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(dstType);
3538  auto srcBaseType = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(srcType);
3539  if (!dstBaseType || !srcBaseType) {
3540  if (dstType != srcType)
3541  return emitError("may not connect different non-base types");
3542  } else {
3543  // Analog types cannot be connected and must be attached.
3544  if (dstBaseType.containsAnalog() || srcBaseType.containsAnalog())
3545  return emitError("analog types may not be connected");
3546 
3547  // Destination and source types must be equivalent.
3548  if (!areTypesEquivalent(dstBaseType, srcBaseType))
3549  return emitError("type mismatch between destination ")
3550  << dstBaseType << " and source " << srcBaseType;
3551 
3552  // Truncation is banned in a connection: destination bit width must be
3553  // greater than or equal to source bit width.
3554  if (!isTypeLarger(dstBaseType, srcBaseType))
3555  return emitError("destination ")
3556  << dstBaseType << " is not as wide as the source " << srcBaseType;
3557  }
3558 
3559  // Check that the flows make sense.
3560  if (failed(checkConnectFlow(*this)))
3561  return failure();
3562 
3563  if (failed(checkConnectConditionality(*this)))
3564  return failure();
3565 
3566  return success();
3567 }

3571  auto baseType = type_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(type);
3572 
3573  // Analog types cannot be connected and must be attached.

3582  }

3585  if (failed(checkConnectFlow(*this)))
3586  return failure();
3587

3589  return failure();
3590

3594 LogicalResult RefDefineOp::verify() {
3595  // Check that the flows make sense.
3596  if (failed(checkConnectFlow(*this)))
3597  return failure();
3598 
3599  // For now, refs can't be in bundles so this is sufficient.
3600  // In the future need to ensure no other define's to same "fieldSource".
3601  // (When aggregates can have references, we can define a reference within,
3602  // but this must be unique. Checking this here may be expensive,
3603  // consider adding something to FModuleLike's to check it there instead)
3604  for (auto *user : getDest().getUsers()) {
3605  if (auto conn = dyn_cast<FConnectLike>(user);
3606  conn && conn.getDest() == getDest() && conn != *this)
3607  return emitError("destination reference cannot be reused by multiple "
3608  "operations, it can only capture a unique dataflow");
3609  }
3610 
3611  // Check "static" source/dest
3612  if (auto *op = getDest().getDefiningOp()) {
3613  // TODO: Make ref.sub only source flow?
3614  if (isa<RefSubOp>(op))
3615  return emitError(
3616  "destination reference cannot be a sub-element of a reference");
3617  if (isa<RefCastOp>(op)) // Source flow, check anyway for now.
3618  return emitError(
3619  "destination reference cannot be a cast of another reference");
3620  }
3621 
3622  // This define is only enabled when its ambient layers are active. Check
3623  // that whenever the destination's layer requirements are met, that this
3624  // op is enabled.
3625  auto ambientLayers = getAmbientLayersAt(getOperation());
3626  auto dstLayers = getLayersFor(getDest());
3627  SmallVector<SymbolRefAttr> missingLayers;
3628  if (!isLayerSetCompatibleWith(ambientLayers, dstLayers, missingLayers)) {
3629  auto diag = emitOpError("has more layer requirements than destination");
3630  auto &note = diag.attachNote();
3631  note << "additional layers required: ";
3632  interleaveComma(missingLayers, note);
3633  return failure();
3634  }
3635 
3636  return success();
3637 }

3684 LogicalResult MatchOp::verify() {
3685  FEnumType type = getInput().getType();
3686 
3687  // Make sure that the number of tags matches the number of regions.
3688  auto numCases = getTags().size();
3689  auto numRegions = getNumRegions();
3690  if (numRegions != numCases)
3691  return emitOpError("expected ")
3692  << numRegions << " tags but got " << numCases;
3693 
3694  auto numTags = type.getNumElements();
3695 
3696  SmallDenseSet<int64_t> seen;
3697  for (const auto &[tag, region] : llvm::zip(getTags(), getRegions())) {
3698  auto tagIndex = size_t(cast<IntegerAttr>(tag).getInt());
3699 
3700  // Ensure that the block has a single argument.
3701  if (region.getNumArguments() != 1)
3702  return emitOpError("region should have exactly one argument");
3703 
3704  // Make sure that it is a valid tag.
3705  if (tagIndex >= numTags)
3706  return emitOpError("the tag index ")
3707  << tagIndex << " is out of the range of valid tags in " << type;
3708 
3709  // Make sure we have not already matched this tag.
3710  auto [it, inserted] = seen.insert(tagIndex);
3711  if (!inserted)
3712  return emitOpError("the tag ") << type.getElementNameAttr(tagIndex)
3713  << " is matched more than once";
3714 
3715  // Check that the block argument type matches the tag's type.
3716  auto expectedType = type.getElementTypePreservingConst(tagIndex);
3717  auto regionType = region.getArgument(0).getType();
3718  if (regionType != expectedType)
3719  return emitOpError("region type ")
3720  << regionType << " does not match the expected type "
3721  << expectedType;
3722  }
3723 
3724  // Check that the match statement is exhaustive.
3725  for (size_t i = 0, e = type.getNumElements(); i < e; ++i)
3726  if (!seen.contains(i))
3727  return emitOpError("missing case for tag ") << type.getElementNameAttr(i);
3728 
3729  return success();
3730 }

3757 ParseResult MatchOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
3758  auto *context = parser.getContext();
3759  OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand input;
3760  if (parser.parseOperand(input) || parser.parseColon())
3761  return failure();
3762 
3763  auto loc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
3764  Type type;
3765  if (parser.parseType(type))
3766  return failure();
3767  auto enumType = type_dyn_cast<FEnumType>(type);
3768  if (!enumType)
3769  return parser.emitError(loc, "expected enumeration type but got") << type;
3770 
3771  if (parser.resolveOperand(input, type, result.operands) ||
3772  parser.parseOptionalAttrDictWithKeyword(result.attributes) ||
3773  parser.parseLBrace())
3774  return failure();
3775 
3776  auto i32Type = IntegerType::get(context, 32);
3777  SmallVector<Attribute> tags;
3778  while (true) {
3779  // Stop parsing when we don't find another "case" keyword.
3780  if (failed(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("case")))
3781  break;
3782 
3783  // Parse the tag and region argument.
3784  auto nameLoc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
3785  std::string name;
3786  OpAsmParser::Argument arg;
3787  auto *region = result.addRegion();
3788  if (parser.parseKeywordOrString(&name) || parser.parseLParen() ||
3789  parser.parseArgument(arg) || parser.parseRParen())
3790  return failure();
3791 
3792  // Figure out the enum index of the tag.
3793  auto index = enumType.getElementIndex(name);
3794  if (!index)
3795  return parser.emitError(nameLoc, "the tag \"")
3796  << name << "\" is not a member of the enumeration " << enumType;
3797  tags.push_back(IntegerAttr::get(i32Type, *index));
3798 
3799  // Parse the region.
3800  arg.type = enumType.getElementTypePreservingConst(*index);
3801  if (parser.parseRegion(*region, arg))
3802  return failure();
3803  }
3804  result.addAttribute("tags", ArrayAttr::get(context, tags));
3805 
3806  return parser.parseRBrace();
3807 }

3911 ParseResult ConstantOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
3912  // Parse the constant value, without knowing its width.
3913  APInt value;
3914  auto loc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
3915  auto valueResult = parser.parseOptionalInteger(value);
3916  if (!valueResult.has_value())
3917  return parser.emitError(loc, "expected integer value");
3918 
3919  // Parse the result firrtl integer type.
3920  IntType resultType;
3921  if (failed(*valueResult) || parser.parseColonType(resultType) ||
3922  parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes))
3923  return failure();
3924  result.addTypes(resultType);
3925 
3926  // Now that we know the width and sign of the result type, we can munge the
3927  // APInt as appropriate.
3928  if (resultType.hasWidth()) {
3929  auto width = (unsigned)resultType.getWidthOrSentinel();
3930  if (width > value.getBitWidth()) {
3931  // sext is always safe here, even for unsigned values, because the
3932  // parseOptionalInteger method will return something with a zero in the
3933  // top bits if it is a positive number.
3934  value = value.sext(width);
3935  } else if (width < value.getBitWidth()) {
3936  // The parser can return an unnecessarily wide result with leading
3937  // zeros. This isn't a problem, but truncating off bits is bad.
3938  unsigned neededBits = value.isNegative() ? value.getSignificantBits()
3939  : value.getActiveBits();
3940  if (width < neededBits)
3941  return parser.emitError(loc, "constant out of range for result type ")
3942  << resultType;
3943  value = value.trunc(width);
3944  }
3945  }
3946 
3947  auto intType = parser.getBuilder().getIntegerType(value.getBitWidth(),
3948  resultType.isSigned());
3949  auto valueAttr = parser.getBuilder().getIntegerAttr(intType, value);
3950  result.addAttribute("value", valueAttr);
3951  return success();
3952 }

3966

4065 // Checks that an array attr representing an aggregate constant has the correct
4066 // shape. This recurses on the type.
4067 static bool checkAggConstant(Operation *op, Attribute attr,
4068  FIRRTLBaseType type) {
4069  if (type.isGround()) {
4070  if (!isa<IntegerAttr>(attr)) {
4071  op->emitOpError("Ground type is not an integer attribute");
4072  return false;
4073  }
4074  return true;
4075  }
4076  auto attrlist = dyn_cast<ArrayAttr>(attr);
4077  if (!attrlist) {
4078  op->emitOpError("expected array attribute for aggregate constant");
4079  return false;
4080  }
4081  if (auto array = type_dyn_cast<FVectorType>(type)) {
4082  if (array.getNumElements() != attrlist.size()) {
4083  op->emitOpError("array attribute (")
4084  << attrlist.size() << ") has wrong size for vector constant ("
4085  << array.getNumElements() << ")";
4086  return false;
4087  }
4088  return llvm::all_of(attrlist, [&array, op](Attribute attr) {
4089  return checkAggConstant(op, attr, array.getElementType());
4090  });
4091  }
4092  if (auto bundle = type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(type)) {
4093  if (bundle.getNumElements() != attrlist.size()) {
4094  op->emitOpError("array attribute (")
4095  << attrlist.size() << ") has wrong size for bundle constant ("
4096  << bundle.getNumElements() << ")";
4097  return false;
4098  }
4099  for (size_t i = 0; i < bundle.getNumElements(); ++i) {
4100  if (bundle.getElement(i).isFlip) {
4101  op->emitOpError("Cannot have constant bundle type with flip");
4102  return false;
4103  }
4104  if (!checkAggConstant(op, attrlist[i], bundle.getElement(i).type))
4105  return false;
4106  }
4107  return true;
4108  }
4109  op->emitOpError("Unknown aggregate type");
4110  return false;
4111 }

4492 /// Return true if the specified operation has a constant value. This trivially
4493 /// checks for `firrtl.constant` and friends, but also looks through subaccesses
4494 /// and correctly handles wires driven with only constant values.
4495 bool firrtl::isConstant(Operation *op) {
4496  // Worklist of ops that need to be examined that should all be constant in
4497  // order for the input operation to be constant.
4498  SmallVector<Operation *, 8> worklist({op});
4499 
4500  // Mutable state indicating if this op is a constant. Assume it is a constant
4501  // and look for counterexamples.
4502  bool constant = true;
4503 
4504  // While we haven't found a counterexample and there are still ops in the
4505  // worklist, pull ops off the worklist. If it provides a counterexample, set
4506  // the `constant` to false (and exit on the next loop iteration). Otherwise,
4507  // look through the op or spawn off more ops to look at.
4508  while (constant && !(worklist.empty()))
4509  TypeSwitch<Operation *>(worklist.pop_back_val())
4510  .Case<NodeOp, AsSIntPrimOp, AsUIntPrimOp>([&](auto op) {
4511  if (auto definingOp = op.getInput().getDefiningOp())
4512  worklist.push_back(definingOp);
4513  constant = false;
4514  })
4515  .Case<WireOp, SubindexOp, SubfieldOp>([&](auto op) {
4516  for (auto &use : op.getResult().getUses())
4517  worklist.push_back(use.getOwner());
4518  })
4519  .Case<ConstantOp, SpecialConstantOp, AggregateConstantOp>([](auto) {})
4520  .Default([&](auto) { constant = false; });
4521 
4522  return constant;
4523 }
4524 
4525 /// Return true if the specified value is a constant. This trivially checks for
4526 /// `firrtl.constant` and friends, but also looks through subaccesses and
4527 /// correctly handles wires driven with only constant values.
4528 bool firrtl::isConstant(Value value) {
4529  if (auto *op = value.getDefiningOp())
4530  return isConstant(op);
4531  return false;
4532 }

4767  IntegerAttr::get(IntegerType::get(context, 32), *index));
4768 
4769  SmallVector<Type> inferredReturnTypes;
4770  if (failed(inferReturnTypes(context, result.location, result.operands,
4771  result.attributes.getDictionary(context),
4772  result.getRawProperties(), result.regions,
4773  inferredReturnTypes)))
4774  return failure();
4775  result.addTypes(inferredReturnTypes);
4776 
4777  return success();
4778 }

4784 /// If LHS and RHS are both UInt or SInt types, the return true and fill in the
4785 /// width of them if known. If unknown, return -1 for the widths.
4786 /// The constness of the result is also returned, where if both lhs and rhs are
4787 /// const, then the result is const.
4788 ///
4789 /// On failure, this reports and error and returns false. This function should
4790 /// not be used if you don't want an error reported.
4791 static bool isSameIntTypeKind(Type lhs, Type rhs, int32_t &lhsWidth,
4792  int32_t &rhsWidth, bool &isConstResult,
4793  std::optional<Location> loc) {
4794  // Must have two integer types with the same signedness.
4795  auto lhsi = type_dyn_cast<IntType>(lhs);
4796  auto rhsi = type_dyn_cast<IntType>(rhs);
4797  if (!lhsi || !rhsi || lhsi.isSigned() != rhsi.isSigned()) {
4798  if (loc) {
4799  if (lhsi && !rhsi)
4800  mlir::emitError(*loc, "second operand must be an integer type, not ")
4801  << rhs;
4802  else if (!lhsi && rhsi)
4803  mlir::emitError(*loc, "first operand must be an integer type, not ")
4804  << lhs;
4805  else if (!lhsi && !rhsi)
4806  mlir::emitError(*loc, "operands must be integer types, not ")
4807  << lhs << " and " << rhs;
4808  else
4809  mlir::emitError(*loc, "operand signedness must match");
4810  }
4811  return false;
4812  }
4813 
4814  lhsWidth = lhsi.getWidthOrSentinel();
4815  rhsWidth = rhsi.getWidthOrSentinel();
4816  isConstResult = lhsi.isConst() && rhsi.isConst();
4817  return true;
4818 }

4822  "SameOperandsIntTypeKind on non-binary op");

4824  bool isConstResult;
4825  return success(isSameIntTypeKind(op->getOperand(0).getType(),
4826  op->getOperand(1).getType(), lhsWidth,
4827  rhsWidth, isConstResult, op->getLoc()));

4955  std::optional<Location> loc) {

5190 
5191 /// Infer the result type for a multiplexer given its two operand types, which
5192 /// may be aggregates.
5193 ///
5194 /// This essentially performs a pairwise comparison of fields and elements, as
5195 /// follows:
5196 /// - Identical operands inferred to their common type
5197 /// - Integer operands inferred to the larger one if both have a known width, a
5198 /// widthless integer otherwise.
5199 /// - Vectors inferred based on the element type.
5200 /// - Bundles inferred in a pairwise fashion based on the field types.
5201 static FIRRTLBaseType inferMuxReturnType(FIRRTLBaseType high,
5202  FIRRTLBaseType low,
5203  bool isConstCondition,
5204  std::optional<Location> loc) {
5205  // If the types are identical we're done.
5206  if (high == low)
5207  return isConstCondition ? low : low.getAllConstDroppedType();
5208 
5209  // The base types need to be equivalent.
5210  if (high.getTypeID() != low.getTypeID())
5211  return emitInferRetTypeError<FIRRTLBaseType>(
5212  loc, "incompatible mux operand types, true value type: ", high,
5213  ", false value type: ", low);
5214 
5215  bool outerTypeIsConst = isConstCondition && low.isConst() && high.isConst();
5216 
5217  // Two different Int types can be compatible. If either has unknown width,
5218  // then return it. If both are known but different width, then return the
5219  // larger one.
5220  if (type_isa<IntType>(low)) {
5221  int32_t highWidth = high.getBitWidthOrSentinel();
5222  int32_t lowWidth = low.getBitWidthOrSentinel();
5223  if (lowWidth == -1)
5224  return low.getConstType(outerTypeIsConst);
5225  if (highWidth == -1)
5226  return high.getConstType(outerTypeIsConst);
5227  return (lowWidth > highWidth ? low : high).getConstType(outerTypeIsConst);
5228  }
5229 
5230  // Infer vector types by comparing the element types.
5231  auto highVector = type_dyn_cast<FVectorType>(high);
5232  auto lowVector = type_dyn_cast<FVectorType>(low);
5233  if (highVector && lowVector &&
5234  highVector.getNumElements() == lowVector.getNumElements()) {
5235  auto inner = inferMuxReturnType(highVector.getElementTypePreservingConst(),
5236  lowVector.getElementTypePreservingConst(),
5237  isConstCondition, loc);
5238  if (!inner)
5239  return {};
5240  return FVectorType::get(inner, lowVector.getNumElements(),
5241  outerTypeIsConst);
5242  }
5243 
5244  // Infer bundle types by inferring names in a pairwise fashion.
5245  auto highBundle = type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(high);
5246  auto lowBundle = type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(low);
5247  if (highBundle && lowBundle) {
5248  auto highElements = highBundle.getElements();
5249  auto lowElements = lowBundle.getElements();
5250  size_t numElements = highElements.size();
5251 
5252  SmallVector<BundleType::BundleElement> newElements;
5253  if (numElements == lowElements.size()) {
5254  bool failed = false;
5255  for (size_t i = 0; i < numElements; ++i) {
5256  if (highElements[i].name != lowElements[i].name ||
5257  highElements[i].isFlip != lowElements[i].isFlip) {
5258  failed = true;
5259  break;
5260  }
5261  auto element = highElements[i];
5262  element.type = inferMuxReturnType(
5263  highBundle.getElementTypePreservingConst(i),
5264  lowBundle.getElementTypePreservingConst(i), isConstCondition, loc);
5265  if (!element.type)
5266  return {};
5267  newElements.push_back(element);
5268  }
5269  if (!failed)
5270  return BundleType::get(low.getContext(), newElements, outerTypeIsConst);
5271  }
5272  return emitInferRetTypeError<FIRRTLBaseType>(
5273  loc, "incompatible mux operand bundle fields, true value type: ", high,
5274  ", false value type: ", low);
5275  }
5276 
5277  // If we arrive here the types of the two mux arms are fundamentally
5278  // incompatible.
5279  return emitInferRetTypeError<FIRRTLBaseType>(
5280  loc, "invalid mux operand types, true value type: ", high,
5281  ", false value type: ", low);
5282 }

5285  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
5286  std::optional<Location> loc) {
5287  auto highType = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(operands[1].getType());
5288  auto lowType = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(operands[2].getType());
5289  if (!highType || !lowType)
5290  return emitInferRetTypeError(loc, "operands must be base type");
5291  return inferMuxReturnType(highType, lowType, isConst(operands[0].getType()),
5292  loc);
5293 }

5306 FIRRTLType Mux4CellIntrinsicOp::inferReturnType(ValueRange operands,
5307  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
5308  std::optional<Location> loc) {
5309  SmallVector<FIRRTLBaseType> types;
5310  FIRRTLBaseType result;
5311  for (unsigned i = 1; i < 5; i++) {
5312  types.push_back(type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(operands[i].getType()));
5313  if (!types.back())
5314  return emitInferRetTypeError(loc, "operands must be base type");
5315  if (result) {
5316  result = inferMuxReturnType(result, types.back(),
5317  isConst(operands[0].getType()), loc);
5318  if (!result)
5319  return result;
5320  } else {
5321  result = types.back();
5322  }
5323  }
5324  return result;
5325 }

5327 FIRRTLType PadPrimOp::inferReturnType(ValueRange operands,
5328  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
5329  std::optional<Location> loc) {
5330  auto input = operands[0].getType();
5331  auto amount = getAttr<IntegerAttr>(attrs, "amount").getValue().getSExtValue();
5332 
5333  auto inputi = type_dyn_cast<IntType>(input);
5334  if (amount < 0 || !inputi)
5335  return emitInferRetTypeError(
5336  loc, "pad input must be integer and amount must be >= 0");
5337 
5338  int32_t width = inputi.getWidthOrSentinel();
5339  if (width == -1)
5340  return inputi;
5341 
5342  width = std::max<int32_t>(width, amount);
5343  return IntType::get(input.getContext(), inputi.isSigned(), width,
5344  inputi.isConst());
5345 }

5347 FIRRTLType ShlPrimOp::inferReturnType(ValueRange operands,

5351  auto amount = getAttr<IntegerAttr>(attrs, "amount").getValue().getSExtValue();
5352 
5353  auto inputi = type_dyn_cast<IntType>(input);
5354  if (amount < 0 || !inputi)
5355  return emitInferRetTypeError(

5366 FIRRTLType ShrPrimOp::inferReturnType(ValueRange operands,
5367  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
5368  std::optional<Location> loc) {
5369  auto input = operands[0].getType();
5370  auto amount = getAttr<IntegerAttr>(attrs, "amount").getValue().getSExtValue();
5371 
5372  auto inputi = type_dyn_cast<IntType>(input);
5373  if (amount < 0 || !inputi)
5374  return emitInferRetTypeError(
5375  loc, "shr input must be integer and amount must be >= 0");
5376 
5377  int32_t width = inputi.getWidthOrSentinel();
5378  if (width != -1) {
5379  // UInt saturates at 0 bits, SInt at 1 bit
5380  int32_t minWidth = inputi.isUnsigned() ? 0 : 1;
5381  width = std::max<int32_t>(minWidth, width - amount);
5382  }
5383 
5384  return IntType::get(input.getContext(), inputi.isSigned(), width,
5385  inputi.isConst());
5386 }

5388 FIRRTLType TailPrimOp::inferReturnType(ValueRange operands,
5389  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
5390  std::optional<Location> loc) {
5391  auto input = operands[0].getType();
5392  auto amount = getAttr<IntegerAttr>(attrs, "amount").getValue().getSExtValue();
5393 
5394  auto inputi = type_dyn_cast<IntType>(input);
5395  if (amount < 0 || !inputi)
5396  return emitInferRetTypeError(
5397  loc, "tail input must be integer and amount must be >= 0");
5398 
5399  int32_t width = inputi.getWidthOrSentinel();
5400  if (width != -1) {
5401  if (width < amount)
5402  return emitInferRetTypeError(
5403  loc, "amount must be less than or equal operand width");
5404  width -= amount;
5405  }
5406 
5407  return IntType::get(input.getContext(), false, width, inputi.isConst());
5408 }

5413 
5414 void VerbatimExprOp::getAsmResultNames(
5415  function_ref<void(Value, StringRef)> setNameFn) {
5416  // If the text is macro like, then use a pretty name. We only take the
5417  // text up to a weird character (like a paren) and currently ignore
5418  // parenthesized expressions.
5419  auto isOkCharacter = [](char c) { return llvm::isAlnum(c) || c == '_'; };
5420  auto name = getText();
5421  // Ignore a leading ` in macro name.
5422  if (name.starts_with("`"))
5423  name = name.drop_front();
5424  name = name.take_while(isOkCharacter);
5425  if (!name.empty())
5426  setNameFn(getResult(), name);
5427 }

5448 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5449 // Conversions to/from structs in the standard dialect.
5450 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5451 
5452 LogicalResult HWStructCastOp::verify() {
5453  // We must have a bundle and a struct, with matching pairwise fields
5454  BundleType bundleType;
5455  hw::StructType structType;
5456  if ((bundleType = type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(getOperand().getType()))) {
5457  structType = getType().dyn_cast<hw::StructType>();
5458  if (!structType)
5459  return emitError("result type must be a struct");
5460  } else if ((bundleType = type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(getType()))) {
5461  structType = getOperand().getType().dyn_cast<hw::StructType>();
5462  if (!structType)
5463  return emitError("operand type must be a struct");
5464  } else {
5465  return emitError("either source or result type must be a bundle type");
5466  }
5467 
5468  auto firFields = bundleType.getElements();
5469  auto hwFields = structType.getElements();
5470  if (firFields.size() != hwFields.size())
5471  return emitError("bundle and struct have different number of fields");
5472 
5473  for (size_t findex = 0, fend = firFields.size(); findex < fend; ++findex) {
5474  if (firFields[findex].name.getValue() != hwFields[findex].name)
5475  return emitError("field names don't match '")
5476  << firFields[findex].name.getValue() << "', '"
5477  << hwFields[findex].name.getValue() << "'";
5478  int64_t firWidth =
5479  FIRRTLBaseType(firFields[findex].type).getBitWidthOrSentinel();
5480  int64_t hwWidth = hw::getBitWidth(hwFields[findex].type);
5481  if (firWidth > 0 && hwWidth > 0 && firWidth != hwWidth)
5482  return emitError("size of field '")
5483  << hwFields[findex].name.getValue() << "' don't match " << firWidth
5484  << ", " << hwWidth;
5485  }
5486 
5487  return success();
5488 }
5489 
5490 LogicalResult BitCastOp::verify() {
5491  auto inTypeBits = getBitWidth(getInput().getType(), /*ignoreFlip=*/true);
5492  auto resTypeBits = getBitWidth(getType());
5493  if (inTypeBits.has_value() && resTypeBits.has_value()) {
5494  // Bitwidths must match for valid bit
5495  if (*inTypeBits == *resTypeBits) {
5496  // non-'const' cannot be casted to 'const'
5497  if (containsConst(getType()) && !isConst(getOperand().getType()))
5498  return emitError("cannot cast non-'const' input type ")
5499  << getOperand().getType() << " to 'const' result type "
5500  << getType();
5501  return success();
5502  }
5503  return emitError("the bitwidth of input (")
5504  << *inTypeBits << ") and result (" << *resTypeBits
5505  << ") don't match";
5506  }
5507  if (!inTypeBits.has_value())
5508  return emitError("bitwidth cannot be determined for input operand type ")
5509  << getInput().getType();
5510  return emitError("bitwidth cannot be determined for result type ")
5511  << getType();
5512 }

5515 // Custom attr-dict Directive that Elides Annotations
5516 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5517 
5518 /// Parse an optional attribute dictionary, adding an empty 'annotations'
5519 /// attribute if not specified.
5520 static ParseResult parseElideAnnotations(OpAsmParser &parser,
5521  NamedAttrList &resultAttrs) {
5522  auto result = parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(resultAttrs);
5523  if (!resultAttrs.get("annotations"))
5524  resultAttrs.append("annotations", parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr({}));
5525 
5526  return result;
5527 }
5528 
5529 static void printElideAnnotations(OpAsmPrinter &p, Operation *op,
5530  DictionaryAttr attr,
5531  ArrayRef<StringRef> extraElides = {}) {
5532  SmallVector<StringRef> elidedAttrs(extraElides.begin(), extraElides.end());
5533  // Elide "annotations" if it is empty.
5534  if (op->getAttrOfType<ArrayAttr>("annotations").empty())
5535  elidedAttrs.push_back("annotations");
5536  // Elide "nameKind".
5537  elidedAttrs.push_back("nameKind");
5538 
5539  p.printOptionalAttrDict(op->getAttrs(), elidedAttrs);
5540 }
5541 
5542 /// Parse an optional attribute dictionary, adding empty 'annotations' and
5543 /// 'portAnnotations' attributes if not specified.
5544 static ParseResult parseElidePortAnnotations(OpAsmParser &parser,
5545  NamedAttrList &resultAttrs) {
5546  auto result = parseElideAnnotations(parser, resultAttrs);
5547 
5548  if (!resultAttrs.get("portAnnotations")) {
5549  SmallVector<Attribute, 16> portAnnotations(
5550  parser.getNumResults(), parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr({}));
5551  resultAttrs.append("portAnnotations",
5552  parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr(portAnnotations));
5553  }
5554  return result;
5555 }
5556 
5557 // Elide 'annotations' and 'portAnnotations' attributes if they are empty.
5558 static void printElidePortAnnotations(OpAsmPrinter &p, Operation *op,
5559  DictionaryAttr attr,
5560  ArrayRef<StringRef> extraElides = {}) {
5561  SmallVector<StringRef, 2> elidedAttrs(extraElides.begin(), extraElides.end());
5562 
5563  if (llvm::all_of(op->getAttrOfType<ArrayAttr>("portAnnotations"),
5564  [&](Attribute a) { return cast<ArrayAttr>(a).empty(); }))
5565  elidedAttrs.push_back("portAnnotations");
5566  printElideAnnotations(p, op, attr, elidedAttrs);
5567 }

5955 FIRRTLType RefSubOp::inferReturnType(ValueRange operands,
5956  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
5957  std::optional<Location> loc) {
5958  auto refType = type_dyn_cast<RefType>(operands[0].getType());
5959  if (!refType)
5960  return emitInferRetTypeError(loc, "input must be of reference type");
5961  auto inType = refType.getType();
5962  auto fieldIdx =
5963  getAttr<IntegerAttr>(attrs, "index").getValue().getZExtValue();
5964 
5965  // TODO: Determine ref.sub + rwprobe behavior, test.
5966  // Probably best to demote to non-rw, but that has implications
5967  // for any LowerTypes behavior being relied on.
5968  // Allow for now, as need to LowerTypes things generally.
5969  if (auto vectorType = type_dyn_cast<FVectorType>(inType)) {
5970  if (fieldIdx < vectorType.getNumElements())
5971  return RefType::get(
5972  vectorType.getElementType().getConstType(
5973  vectorType.isConst() || vectorType.getElementType().isConst()),
5974  refType.getForceable(), refType.getLayer());
5975  return emitInferRetTypeError(loc, "out of range index '", fieldIdx,
5976  "' in RefType of vector type ", refType);
5977  }
5978  if (auto bundleType = type_dyn_cast<BundleType>(inType)) {
5979  if (fieldIdx >= bundleType.getNumElements()) {
5980  return emitInferRetTypeError(loc,
5981  "subfield element index is greater than "
5982  "the number of fields in the bundle type");
5983  }
5984  return RefType::get(bundleType.getElement(fieldIdx).type.getConstType(
5985  bundleType.isConst() ||
5986  bundleType.getElement(fieldIdx).type.isConst()),
5987  refType.getForceable(), refType.getLayer());
5988  }
5989 
5990  return emitInferRetTypeError(
5991  loc, "ref.sub op requires a RefType of vector or bundle base type");
5992 }

6024 LogicalResult RWProbeOp::verifyInnerRefs(hw::InnerRefNamespace &ns) {
6025  auto targetRef = getTarget();
6026  if (targetRef.getModule() !=
6027  (*this)->getParentOfType<FModuleLike>().getModuleNameAttr())
6028  return emitOpError() << "has non-local target";
6029 
6030  auto target = ns.lookup(targetRef);
6031  if (!target)
6032  return emitOpError() << "has target that cannot be resolved: " << targetRef;
6033 
6034  auto checkFinalType = [&](auto type, Location loc) -> LogicalResult {
6035  // Determine final type.
6036  mlir::Type fType =
6037  hw::FieldIdImpl::getFinalTypeByFieldID(type, target.getField());
6038  // Check.
6039  auto baseType = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(fType);
6040  if (!baseType || baseType.getPassiveType() != getType().getType()) {
6041  auto diag = emitOpError("has type mismatch: target resolves to ")
6042  << fType << " instead of expected " << getType().getType();
6043  diag.attachNote(loc) << "target resolves here";
6044  return diag;
6045  }
6046  return success();
6047  };
6048  if (target.isPort()) {
6049  auto mod = cast<FModuleLike>(target.getOp());
6050  return checkFinalType(mod.getPortType(target.getPort()),
6051  mod.getPortLocation(target.getPort()));
6052  }
6053  hw::InnerSymbolOpInterface symOp =
6054  cast<hw::InnerSymbolOpInterface>(target.getOp());
6055  if (!symOp.getTargetResult())
6056  return emitOpError("has target that cannot be probed")
6057  .attachNote(symOp.getLoc())
6058  .append("target resolves here");
6059  auto *ancestor =
6060  symOp.getTargetResult().getParentBlock()->findAncestorOpInBlock(**this);
6061  if (!ancestor || !symOp->isBeforeInBlock(ancestor))
6062  return emitOpError("is not dominated by target")
6063  .attachNote(symOp.getLoc())
6064  .append("target here");
6065  return checkFinalType(symOp.getTargetResult().getType(), symOp.getLoc());
6066 }

6072 LogicalResult LayerBlockOp::verify() {
6073  auto layerName = getLayerName();
6074  auto *parentOp = (*this)->getParentOp();
6075 
6076  // Verify the correctness of the symbol reference. Only verify that this
6077  // layer block makes sense in its parent module or layer block.
6078  auto nestedReferences = layerName.getNestedReferences();
6079  if (nestedReferences.empty()) {
6080  if (!isa<FModuleOp>(parentOp)) {
6081  auto diag = emitOpError() << "has an un-nested layer symbol, but does "
6082  "not have a 'firrtl.module' op as a parent";
6083  return diag.attachNote(parentOp->getLoc())
6084  << "illegal parent op defined here";
6085  }
6086  } else {
6087  auto parentLayerBlock = dyn_cast<LayerBlockOp>(parentOp);
6088  if (!parentLayerBlock) {
6089  auto diag = emitOpError()
6090  << "has a nested layer symbol, but does not have a '"
6091  << getOperationName() << "' op as a parent'";
6092  return diag.attachNote(parentOp->getLoc())
6093  << "illegal parent op defined here";
6094  }
6095  auto parentLayerBlockName = parentLayerBlock.getLayerName();
6096  if (parentLayerBlockName.getRootReference() !=
6097  layerName.getRootReference() ||
6098  parentLayerBlockName.getNestedReferences() !=
6099  layerName.getNestedReferences().drop_back()) {
6100  auto diag = emitOpError() << "is nested under an illegal layer block";
6101  return diag.attachNote(parentLayerBlock->getLoc())
6102  << "illegal parent layer block defined here";
6103  }
6104  }
6105 
6106  // Verify the body of the region.
6107  auto result = getBody(0)->walk<mlir::WalkOrder::PreOrder>(
6108  [&](Operation *op) -> WalkResult {
6109  // Skip nested layer blocks. Those will be verified separately.
6110  if (isa<LayerBlockOp>(op))
6111  return WalkResult::skip();
6112 
6113  // Check all the operands of each op to make sure that only legal things
6114  // are captured.
6115  for (auto operand : op->getOperands()) {
6116  // Any value captured from the current layer block is fine.
6117  if (auto *definingOp = operand.getDefiningOp())
6118  if (getOperation()->isAncestor(definingOp))
6119  continue;
6120 
6121  auto type = operand.getType();
6122 
6123  // Capture of a non-base type, e.g., reference, is allowed.
6124  if (isa<PropertyType>(type)) {
6125  auto diag = emitOpError() << "captures a property operand";
6126  diag.attachNote(operand.getLoc()) << "operand is defined here";
6127  diag.attachNote(op->getLoc()) << "operand is used here";
6128  return WalkResult::interrupt();
6129  }
6130 
6131  // Capturing a non-passive type is illegal.
6132  if (auto baseType = type_dyn_cast<FIRRTLBaseType>(type)) {
6133  if (!baseType.isPassive()) {
6134  auto diag = emitOpError()
6135  << "captures an operand which is not a passive type";
6136  diag.attachNote(operand.getLoc()) << "operand is defined here";
6137  diag.attachNote(op->getLoc()) << "operand is used here";
6138  return WalkResult::interrupt();
6139  }
6140  }
6141  }
6142 
6143  // Ensure that the layer block does not drive any sinks outside.
6144  if (auto connect = dyn_cast<FConnectLike>(op)) {
6145  // ref.define is allowed to drive probes outside the layerblock.
6146  if (isa<RefDefineOp>(connect))
6147  return WalkResult::advance();
6148 
6149  // We can drive any destination inside the current layerblock.
6150  auto dest = getFieldRefFromValue(connect.getDest()).getValue();
6151  if (auto *destOp = dest.getDefiningOp())
6152  if (getOperation()->isAncestor(destOp))
6153  return WalkResult::advance();
6154 
6155  auto diag =
6156  connect.emitOpError()
6157  << "connects to a destination which is defined outside its "
6158  "enclosing layer block";
6159  diag.attachNote(getLoc()) << "enclosing layer block is defined here";
6160  diag.attachNote(dest.getLoc()) << "destination is defined here";
6161  return WalkResult::interrupt();
6162  }
6163 
6164  return WalkResult::advance();
6165  });
6166 
6167  return failure(result.wasInterrupted());
6168 }
